  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Cosmos', 'CO-21', 'Galactic Glacier', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'CO-21 Galactic Glacier is a highly fluid light blue glaze with iridescent crystals that flash pink, violet, and silver.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2376/4599/CO-21_GalacticGlacier_Square_WEB__16140.1772228354.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Cosmos', 'CO-24', 'Blue Starlight', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'CO-24 is a highly fluid dark blue glaze with delicate crystals.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2377/4602/CO-24_BlueStarlight_Square_WEB__14341.1772229294.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Crawls', 'CR-1', 'Black', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'CR-1 is a glossy black glaze that, when fired, crawls into raised shapes of varying sizes and forms. The result is a surface marked by unpredictable, natural patterns that add unique texture and visual interest to each piece. The featured chip image of CR-1 is applied on AMACO No.11 A-Mix White Stoneware. Layering sample images are 2 coats over 2 coats, fired to Cone 6 Apply 1-4 even coats of glaze to cone 04 bisque. Allow each coat to dry almost fully, but before any significant cracking occurs. Crawl glazes will develop hairline cracks as they dry; handle with care. For added durability before firing, layer over an AMACO Celadon glaze or underglaze More coats create larger glaze dots, while thinner coats produce a finer bead effect. Increased coats will produce more cracks. Fire to cone 5-6 for best results These glazes are food safe when layered over AMACO Celadons.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2354/4084/CR-1_Black_1280pxX1280px_Website__07874.1747311865.jpg?c=1'),
