  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Dipping & Layering', 'DL-01', 'Ebony', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'DL-1 Ebony is an opaque glossy black glaze, great as a base for layering or on its own While measuring the specific gravity is not required to initially mix the AMACO Dipping and Layering glazes, there may be a time you need to know the recommended specific gravity for DL-01 Ebony is 1.53.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2268/3604/DL-1_Ebony_WebsiteSwatch__18812.1707143222.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Dipping & Layering', 'DL-10', 'Gloss Clear', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'ORDER AT YOUR LOCAL DISTRIBUTOR DL-10 Gloss Clear is a transparent glaze, great for adding a glossy shine While measuring the specific gravity is not required to initially mix the AMACO Dipping and Layering glazes, there may be a time you need to know the recommended specific gravity for DL-10 Gloss Clear is 1.51.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2372/4570/DL-10_Square_Website__34292.1770402654.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Dipping & Layering', 'DL-11', 'Enamel White', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'DL-11 Enamel White is a gloss white glaze, great as a liner, a base for layering, or on its own While measuring the specific gravity is not required to initially mix the AMACO Dipping and Layering glazes, there may be a time you need to know the recommended specific gravity for DL-11 Enamel White is 1.53.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2269/3608/DL-11_EnamelWhite_WebsiteSwatch__88926.1707144340.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Dipping & Layering', 'DL-12', 'Midnight Blue', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'DL-12 Midnight Blue is a glossy, deep navy blue glaze that breaks into lighter blue highlights where thick. This glaze is good for textured work and layers well with other DL glazes While measuring the specific gravity is not required to initially mix the AMACO Dipping and Layering glazes, there may be a time you need to know the recommended specific gravity for DL-12 Midnight Blue is 1.52.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2343/3925/DL-12_MidnightBlue_SquareTile_WEB__92818.1733273545.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Dipping & Layering', 'DL-20', 'Floating Blue', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'DL-20 Floating Blue is a classic blue glaze that is pale where thick, darker blue where thinner, and breaks iron brown While measuring the specific gravity is not required to initially mix the AMACO Dipping and Layering glazes, there may be a time you need to know the recommended specific gravity for DL-20 Floating Blue is 1.52.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2270/3612/DL-20_FloatingBlue_WebsiteSwatch__07510.1707144984.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Dipping & Layering', 'DL-23', 'Ultramarine', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'DL-23 Ultramarine is a glossy cobalt blue glaze with a lighter float. Moves when fired and breaks gray where thin. Beautiful for layering or alone While measuring the specific gravity is not required to initially mix the AMACO Dipping and Layering glazes, there may be a time you need to know the recommended specific gravity for DL-23 Ultramarine is 1.52.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2271/3614/DL-23_Ultramarine_WebsiteSamplePiece__18761.1719949340.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Dipping & Layering', 'DL-25', 'Coastline', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'DL-25 Coastline is a glossy turquoise glaze that transitions to a green- beige hue where thin. Great for adding depth to textured pieces and layers well with other DL glazes While measuring the specific gravity is not required to initially mix the AMACO Dipping and Layering glazes, there may be a time you need to know the recommended specific gravity for DL-25 Coastline is 1.52 MIXING DIRECTIONS: Wear a NIOSH approved mask for dust. Pour 1 gallon (3.8L) of distilled water into a 2 gallon (7.6L) or larger bucket. Avoid breathing dust while adding product to water. Mix contents until smooth and free of lumps.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2344/3926/DL-25_Coastline_SquareTile_WEB__25849.1733274023.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Dipping & Layering', 'DL-27', 'Storm Cloud', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'DL-27 Storm Cloud is a deep navy glaze that pools and accentuates texture. This glaze is beautiful by itself or when layered to create an oil spot effect While measuring the specific gravity is not required to initially mix the AMACO Dipping and Layering glazes, there may be a time you need to know the recommended specific gravity for DL-27 Storm Cloud is 1.54 MIXING DIRECTIONS: Wear a NIOSH approved mask for dust. Pour 1 gallon (3.8L) of distilled water into a 2 gallon (7.6L) or larger bucket. Avoid breathing dust while adding product to water. Mix contents until smooth and free of lumps.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2345/3927/DL-27_StormCloud_SquareTile_WEB__02143.1733274549.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Dipping & Layering', 'DL-33', 'Low Tide', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'DL-33 Low Tide is a glossy iron glaze, transparent brown where thin and gray-green where thick. Great as a base coat for dramatic layering glazes or alone, highlights texture While measuring the specific gravity is not required to initially mix the AMACO Dipping and Layering glazes, there may be a time you need to know the recommended specific gravity for DL-33 Low Tide is 1.54.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2272/3622/DL-33LowTide_WebsiteSwatch__07980.1707148501.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Dipping & Layering', 'DL-42', 'River Moss', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'DL-42 River Moss is a glossy deep green opaque glaze, that breaks clear where thin. Some movement when fired, beautiful as a layering top coat or alone While measuring the specific gravity is not required to initially mix the AMACO Dipping and Layering glazes, there may be a time you need to know the recommended specific gravity for DL-42 River Moss is 1.52.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2273/3625/DL-42RiverMoss_WebsiteSwatch__49688.1707149260.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Dipping & Layering', 'DL-57', 'Mulberry Mist', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'ORDER AT YOUR LOCAL DISTRIBUTOR DL-57 Mulberry Mist is a warm, dark purple glaze with a soft float of lilac over the surface While measuring the specific gravity is not required to initially mix the AMACO Dipping and Layering glazes, there may be a time you need to know the recommended specific gravity for DL-57 Mulberry Mist is 1.53.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2373/4571/DL-57_Square_Website__29831.1770403029.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Dipping & Layering', 'DL-59', 'Brick Red', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'DL-59 Brick Red is an opaque vivid red speckled glaze that breaks translucent where thin. This bold color is great on its own or layered with other DL glazes While measuring the specific gravity is not required to initially mix the AMACO Dipping and Layering glazes, there may be a time you need to know the recommended specific gravity for DL-59 Brick Red is 1.58 MIXING DIRECTIONS: Wear a NIOSH approved mask for dust. Pour 1 gallon (3.8L) of distilled water into a 2 gallon (7.6L) or larger bucket. Avoid breathing dust while adding product to water. Mix contents until smooth and free of lumps.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2346/3928/DL-59_BrickRed_SquareTile_WEB__04921.1733275131.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Dipping & Layering', 'DL-60', 'Honeycomb', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'DL-60 Honeycomb is a satiny golden-yellow glaze with a darker texture where thicker. Some movement when fired. Lovely as an accent or base for layering While measuring the specific gravity is not required to initially mix the AMACO Dipping and Layering glazes, there may be a time you need to know the recommended specific gravity for DL-60 Honeycomb is 1.58.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2274/3630/DL-60_Honeycomb_WebsiteSwatch__63508.1707151007.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Dipping & Layering', 'DL-63', 'Stardust', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'DL-63 Stardust is a dark brown and black glaze with sparkles that shift between silver and copper. This glaze works well as a base or top layer when paired with other DL glazes While measuring the specific gravity is not required to initially mix the AMACO Dipping and Layering glazes, there may be a time you need to know the recommended specific gravity for DL-63 Stardust is 1.60.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2347/3929/DL-63_Stardust_SquareTile_WEB__67917.1733275402.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Dipping & Layering', 'DL-70', 'Oxblood', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'DL-70 Oxblood is a reduction copper red glaze in oxidation firing and breaks clear. Needs thick application to develop Oxblood red. This glaze may run While measuring the specific gravity is not needed for the Dipping & Layering due to their formulation, the specific gravity for DL-70 Oxblood is 1.51.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2275/3632/DL-70_Oxblood_6x6_SquareTile_WEB__42162.1707151622.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Dipping Glazes', 'DC-10', 'Low-Fire Dipping Clear (Liquid)', 'Cone 05', 'Formulated especially for dipping, this glaze will stop running as soon as it is lifted out of the glaze bucket. Application is uniform and there is no waiting for it to drip or dry. Fire to Cone 05.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/542/2532/DC-10_Clear_Glaze__27674.1659457728.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'High Fire', 'HF-01', 'Black', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'HF-1 Black is a glossy, opaque black glaze. HF Black is food-safe, safe for spray application, and great as a liner or even a base for layering other glazes. Suitable for firing cone 5 and up.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2296/3691/HF-1_Black_37000A_6x6_Square_Tile_WEB__79155.1708018287.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'High Fire', 'HF-09', 'Zinc-Free Clear', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'Zinc-Free Clear is a glossy glaze recommended for use with underglazes to reduce the incidence of color shift. Most underglazes, stains, and coloring oxides will show their best color with Zinc-Free Clear.Some colors may be muted with HF-9 Zinc-Free Clear: V-315 Peach V-316 Light Pink V-323 Salmon *.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/453/2695/Vase_Mini_HF-9_Jensen__56478.1659533864.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'High Fire', 'HF-10', 'Clear', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'HF-10 Clear is a shiny bright glaze with zinc for hardness. A fabulous liner glaze or for use with cadmium underglazes Colors which work well with HF-10 Clear are: V-387 Bright Red V-388 Radiant Red V-389 Flame Orange V-390 Bright Orange V-391 Intense Yellow Colors which may shift when used with HF-10 Clear: LUG-15 Warm Gray LUG-42 Blue Green LUG-43 Dark Green V-333 Avocado V-353 Dark Green V-366 Teddy Bear Brown V-376 Hunter Green.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2297/3692/HF-10_Clear_37001B_6x6_Square_Tile_WEB__15248.1708018570.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'High Fire', 'HF-11', 'White', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'White is a glossy opaque white glaze. HF White is food-safe, safe for spray application, and great as a liner or even a base for layering other glazes. Suitable for firing cone 5 and up.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2298/3693/HF-11_White_37002C_6x6_Square_Tile_WEB__42744.1708018713.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'High Fire', 'HF-125', 'Turquoise', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'HF Turquoise is a stiff, glossy, opaque light aqua glaze. Originally part of the Celebration line, a series inspired by the classic Fiesta tableware ceramics, HF125 Turquoise is food-safe, safe for spray application, and great as a liner or even a base for layering other glazes. Suitable for firing cone 5 and up.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2299/3694/HF-125_Turquoise_35505E_6x6_Square_Tile_WEB__99015.1708018968.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'High Fire', 'HF-127', 'China Blue', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'China Blue is a stiff, glossy, opaque medium blue glaze. Originally part of the Celebration line, a series inspired by the classic Fiesta tableware ceramics, China Blue is food-safe, safe for spray application, and great as a liner or even a base for layering other glazes. Suitable for firing cone 5 and up.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2301/3696/HF-127_China_Blue_35503A_6x6_Square_Tile_WEB__02160.1708020069.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'High Fire', 'HF-129', 'Baby Blue', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'Baby Blue is a stiff, glossy, sky blue glaze. Originally part of the Celebration line, a series inspired by the classic Fiesta tableware ceramics, Baby Blue is food-safe, safe for spray application, and great as a liner or even a base for layering other glazes. Suitable for firing cone 5 and up.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2300/3695/HF-129_Baby_Blue_35506F_6x6_Square_Tile_WEB__07507.1708019910.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'High Fire', 'HF-142', 'Chartreuse', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'Chartreuse is a stiff, glossy, opaque lime green glaze.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2302/3697/HF-142_Chartreuse_35510M_6x6_Square_Tile_WEB__97561.1708020213.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'High Fire', 'HF-161', 'Bright Yellow', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'Bright Yellow is an opaque, lemon colored glaze that has a consistent, reliable result that is great for classrooms Originally part of the Celebration line, a series inspired by the classic Fiesta tableware ceramics, Bright Yellow is food-safe, safe for spray application, and great as a liner or even a base for layering other glazes. Suitable for firing cone 5 and up Several artists have experimented with the Celebration glazes in wood, soda, and salt at temperatures up to cone 12, which yielded great results! Make sure you always test when exploring alternative firings for any of AMACO''s glazes.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/429/2712/HF-161_Bright_Yellow_Bowl_sized__41094.1659536247.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'High Fire', 'HF-165', 'Scarlet Red', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'Scarlet Red is an opaque, crimson glaze that has a consistent, reliable result that is great for classrooms Originally part of the Celebration line, a series inspired by the classic Fiesta tableware ceramics, Scarlet Red is food-safe, safe for spray application, and great as a liner or even a base for layering other glazes. Suitable for firing cone 5 and up Several artists have experimented with the Celebration glazes in wood, soda, and salt at temperatures up to cone 12, which yielded great results! Make sure you always test when exploring alternative firings for any of AMACO''s glazes.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/431/2711/HF-165_Scarlet_Red_Round_Plate_sized__92264.1659536080.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'High Fire', 'HF-166', 'Orangerie', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'Orangerie is an opaque, yellow-orange glaze that has a consistent, reliable result that is great for classrooms. Originally part of the Celebration line, a series inspired by the classic Fiesta tableware ceramics, Orangerie is food-safe, safe for spray application, and great as a liner or even a base for layering other glazes. Suitable for firing cone 5 and up Several artists have experimented with the Celebration glazes in wood, soda, and salt at temperatures up to cone 12, which yielded great results! Make sure you always test when exploring alternative firings for any of AMACO''s glazes.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/432/2709/HF-166_Orangerie_Square_Plate_sized__93324.1659535939.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'High Fire', 'HF-167', 'Clementine', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'Clementine is an opaque, vibrant orange glaze that has a consistent, reliable result that is great for classrooms. Originally part of the Celebration line, a series inspired by the classic Fiesta tableware ceramics, Clementine is food-safe, safe for spray application, and great as a liner or even a base for layering other glazes. Suitable for firing cone 5 and up Several artists have experimented with the Celebration glazes in wood, soda, and salt at temperatures up to cone 12, which yielded great results! Make sure you always test when exploring alternative firings for any of AMACO''s glazes.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/433/2706/HF-167_Clementtine_Bowl_sized__97160.1659535817.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'High Fire', 'HF-170', 'Lilac', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'Lilac is an opaque, light purple glaze that has a consistent, reliable result that is great for classrooms. Due to the purple pigment, this glaze might lose some of it''s intensity at higher temperatures. Originally part of the Celebration line, a series inspired by the classic Fiesta tableware ceramics, Lilac is food-safe, safe for spray application, and great as a liner or even a base for layering other glazes. Suitable for firing cone 5 and up Several artists have experimented with the Celebration glazes in wood, soda, and salt at temperatures up to cone 12, which yielded great results! Make sure you always test when exploring alternative firings for any of AMACO''s glazes.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/435/2704/HF-170_Lilac_Bowl_sized__06176.1659535585.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'High Fire', 'HF-171', 'Amethyst', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'Amethyst is an opaque, dark purple glaze that has a consistent, reliable result that is great for classrooms. Due to the purple pigment Amethyst might lose some of the rich purple color when fired at a higher temperature. Originally part of the Celebration line, a series inspired by the classic Fiesta tableware ceramics, Amethyst is food-safe, safe for spray application, and great as a liner or even a base for layering other glazes. Suitable for firing cone 5 and up Several artists have experimented with the Celebration glazes in wood, soda, and salt at temperatures up to cone 12, which yielded great results! Make sure you always test when exploring alternative firings for any of AMACO''s glazes.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/436/2701/HF-171_Amethyst_Round_Plate_sized__21776.1659535443.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'High Fire', 'HF-26', 'Turquoise', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'Turquoise is an intense, satin teal glaze that produces intense color and attractive high-fire effects at mid-range temperatures. Originally part of the Sahara line.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/441/2699/Vase_Mini_HF-26_Jensen__26472.1659535051.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'High Fire', 'HF-55', 'Coral', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'Coral is a glossy, vibrant persimmon-colored glaze that produces intense color and attractive high-fire effects at mid-range temperatures.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/447/2698/Vase_Mini_HF-55_Jensen__70089.1659534600.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'High Fire', 'HF-56', 'Red Gloss', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6', 'Red Gloss is a glossy deep red glaze that produces intense color and attractive high-fire effects at mid range temperatures.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/448/2697/Vase_Mini_HF-56_Jensen__48059.1659534449.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Kiln Ice', 'KI-11', 'Snow Drift', null, 'KI -11 Snow Drift is a diffused, milky white glaze The Kiln Ice glazes are modeled after traditional Guan or Snowflake glazes. They feature a delicate network of fine hairline cracks (known as “crazing”). Kiln Ice glazes are translucent, but become slightly opaque where the cracks form, creating a beautiful, multi-layered visual texture. Differences in glaze application and firing technique may affect end results These glazes are food safe, but due to durability, they are not recommended for food surfaces.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2348/3945/KI-11_3C_over32M_Cone5_WEB__58637.1741099636.jpg?c=1'),
