  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Liquid Underglaze', 'LUG-42', 'Blue Green', 'Cone 05', 'Blue Green Liquid Underglaze is a deep teal that is soft and light at cone 05, becomes a much deeper blue green and fluxes into a soft glaze-like surface at cone 6, and maintains that deeper tone with a soft sheen at cone 10. Though the underglaze does become glaze-like, a clear gloss glaze can give Blue Green an impeccably smooth surface with good color For Blue Green Liquid Underglaze, we recommend using HF-9 Zinc Free Clear. If HF-10 Clear is used, color may shift HF-9 Zinc-Free Clear is recommended for use with underglazes to reduce the incidence of color shift. Most underglazes, stains, and coloring oxides will show their best color with Zinc-Free Clear.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/779/1562/41153B__52630.1659282844.jpg?c=1'),
