  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Teacher''s Palette Light', 'TPL-63', 'Citrine', 'Cone 05', 'Citrine is a translucent, lemon yellow glaze that boasts a glossy, smooth surface after firing. 100% mixable and true to their unfired color, the Teacher’s Palette Light® glazes are a must-have for any classroom or studio. These glazes look especially beautiful over carved and textured surfaces. In need of a fun project? Try brushing one layer of any of the Teacher’s Palette Light colors over a design created with one of our Velvet Underglazes.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2251/3564/TPL-63_Citrine__82883.1694487536.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Teacher''s Palette Light', 'TPL-66', 'Fire Opal', 'Cone 05', 'Fire Opal is a translucent, vermillion orange glaze that boasts a glossy, smooth surface after firing. 100% mixable and true to their unfired color, the Teacher’s Palette Light® glazes are a must-have for any classroom or studio. These glazes look especially beautiful over carved and textured surfaces. In need of a fun project? Try brushing one layer of any of the Teacher’s Palette Light colors over a design created with one of our Velvet Underglazes.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2252/3565/TPL-66_Fire-Opal__20883.1694487537.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Texturizer', 'TH-1', 'High Fire Texturizer', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6 / Cone 05', 'TH-1 is a rutile-based glaze changer. When layered with other glazes, it tends to produce a golden matte surface. Apply one thin coat of Texturizer under or over another glaze and fire to cone 5 or higher.TH-1 is LEAD FREE and Non Toxic.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/758/1676/large_PC-55_over_TH-1__71219.1659289052.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Texturizer', 'TL-1', 'Low Fire Texturizer', 'Cone 5 / Cone 6 / Cone 05', 'Apply TL-1 Texturizer over any Cone 05 glaze to create different textures. Surface textures vary depending on the type of base glaze (gloss, matte, or textured), broadening the glaze palette tremendously. An even wider variety of effects can be achieved by applying TL-1 between coats of two different Cone 05 glazes.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/759/1671/TL1oLG24__40273.1659287793.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Sprayz', 'VS-308', 'Yellow', 'Cone 05 / Cone 10', 'VS-308 Yellow Velvet Sprayz underglaze is a bright lemon yellow that is vivid at cone 05. It is still bright, but less saturated at cone 05 and becomes pale at cone 10. A clear glaze over Yellow darkens the color slightly, but has less of an effect at higher temperatures Velvet Sprayz are available in 10oz cans The Velvet Sprayz are currently only available to ship within the contiguous U.S.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2327/3872/VelvetSprayz_ProductImages_Yellow_WEB__58768.1726578026.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Sprayz', 'VS-326', 'Medium Blue', 'Cone 05 / Cone 10', 'VS-326 Medium Blue Velvet Sprayz underglaze is a brilliant primary blue that is vivid at cone 05, darker at cone 5, maintaining its blue color. A clear glaze over Medium Blue will significantly darken the color at any temperature Velvet Sprayz are available in 10oz cans The Velvet Sprayz are currently only available to ship within the contiguous U.S.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2328/3874/VelvetSprayz_ProductImages_MediumBlue_WEB__53194.1726770660.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Sprayz', 'VS-353', 'Dark Green', 'Cone 05 / Cone 10', 'VS-353 Dark Green Velvet Sprayz underglaze is a rich green color that is bright and saturated at cone 05, darkens to a forest green at cone 5, and becomes slightly darker at cone 10. A clear glaze deepens the color of the underglaze significantly at any temperature Velvet Sprayz are available in 10oz cans. The Velvet Sprayz are currently only available to ship within the contiguous U.S.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2329/3880/VelvetSprayz_ProductImages_DarkGreen_WEB__00671.1726771767.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Sprayz', 'VS-359', 'Ultra White', 'Cone 05 / Cone 10', 'VS-359 Ultra White Velvet Sprayz underglaze is a bright and opaque white at cone 05, a frosty color at cone 5, and maintains its vividness at cone 10. A clear glaze accentuates the color of the underglaze significantly at any temperature Velvet Sprayz are available in 10oz cans. The Velvet Sprayz are currently only available to ship within the contiguous U.S.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2330/3878/VelvetSprayz_ProductImages_UltraWhite_WEB__40535.1726771736.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Sprayz', 'VS-361', 'Jet Black', 'Cone 05 / Cone 10', 'VS-361 Jet Black Velvet Sprayz underglaze is a cool black color that is smooth and velvety at cone 05, darkens at cone 5, and becomes darkest black and slightly glossy at cone 10. A clear glaze deepens and accentuates the underglaze significantly at any temperature Velvet Sprayz are available in 10oz cans. The Velvet Sprayz are currently only available to ship within the contiguous U.S.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2331/3882/VelvetSprayz_ProductImages_JetBlack_WEB__71833.1726771923.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Sprayz', 'VS-384', 'Real Orange', 'Cone 05 / Cone 10', 'VS-384 Real Orange Velvet Sprayz underglaze is a luminous orange color that is bright and saturated at cone 05, softens and becomes lighter at cone 5 and becomes slightly warmer and is still bright at cone 10. A clear glaze accentuates the color of the underglaze significantly at any temperature Velvet Sprayz are available in 10oz cans. The Velvet Sprayz are currently only available to ship within the contiguous U.S.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2332/3884/VelvetSprayz_ProductImages_RealOrange_WEB__46859.1726772107.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Sprayz', 'VS-387', 'Bright Red', 'Cone 05 / Cone 10', 'VS-387 Bright Red Velvet Sprayz underglaze is a deep crimson color that is vivid at cone 05, darkens slightly at cone 5, and becomes a deep cherry red at cone 10. A clear glaze deepens the color and accentuates the underglaze nicely at any temperature Velvet Sprayz are available in 10oz cans The Velvet Sprayz are currently only available to ship within the contiguous U.S.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2333/3886/VelvetSprayz_ProductImages_BrightRed_WEB__36249.1726772272.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-301', 'Ivory Beige Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Ivory Beige Velvet Underglaze is a soft cream color that is very light at cone 05. It warms up a little at cone 5, but burns out almost completely at cone 10. A clear glaze over Ivory Beige accentuates and darkens the color at cone 05 and cone 5. At cone 10, there is no color change between glazed and unglazed.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2119/3314/37400A__35979.1663233214.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-303', 'Terra Cotta Underglazes', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Terra Cotta Velvet Underglaze is a warm cinnamon brown that is much darker with a clear glaze on top at any temperature. At cone 05, it is red-brown and reminiscent of the clay it is named after. It darkens at cone 5 and becomes a deep chocolate color at cone 10.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2110/3296/37402C__75678.1663222564.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-304', 'Straw Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Straw Velvet Underglaze is a rich sunflower yellow that is a strong ochre at cone 05 and becomes lighter at cone 5. At cone 10, it is even lighter and less saturated. Overall, it maintains its color well at any temperature and becomes richer and darker under a clear glaze.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2111/3299/37403D__50124.1663223152.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-308', 'Yellow Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Yellow Velvet Underglaze is a bright lemon yellow that is vivid at cone 05. It is still bright, but less saturated at cone 05 and becomes pale at cone 10. A clear glaze over Yellow darkens the color slightly, but has less of an effect at higher temperatures.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2112/3301/37404E__02275.1663223488.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-309', 'Deep Yellow Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Deep Yellow Velvet Underglaze is a rich ochre color that is very rich at cone 05 and is intense under a clear glaze. At cone 5, it is less saturated and becomes muted and darker at cone 10.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/798/1494/37405F__22527.1659278734.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-311', 'Nectar Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Nectar underglaze is a warm yellow color like honeysuckle flowers at cone 05 and becomes more light amber under a clear glaze. It slightly intensifies at cone 5 and cone 10.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2278/3647/V-311_Nectar_Cone5_WebsiteSwatch__44106.1707163072.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-313', 'Red Brown Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Red Brown Velvet Underglaze is a warm cocoa color that is reddish at cone 05. The color darkens at cone 5, and becomes chocolatey at cone 10. A clear glaze deepens the color of the underglaze significantly at any temperature.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2115/3307/37407H__84160.1663224333.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-314', 'Chocolate Brown Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Chocolate Brown Velvet Underglaze is a deep brown that is warmest at cone 05. The color darkens at cone 5, and is darkest but less saturated at cone 10. This underglaze looks great beneath a few coats of a clear glaze.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2116/3309/37408J__32008.1663224688.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-315', 'Peach Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Peach Velvet Underglaze is a warm pink at cone 05 that darkens slightly at cone 5, and becomes a light coral at cone 10. A clear glaze darkens the color slightly at any temperature Peach Velvet Underglaze may be muted when used under C-11 Mixing Clear Originally formulated to dilute the color of Celadon series glazes, C-11 Mixing Clear can be used as a clear glaze. Mixing Clear is a stiff gloss glaze that works well with most underglazes.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2117/3311/37410L__58937.1663225026.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-317', 'Coral Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Coral is a warm, bright pink underglaze that retains color from cone 05 up to cone 10 with minimal darkening. Clear glaze brightens the color. Can be used with zinc or non-zinc glazes without color shift.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2118/3313/V-317_Coral_Color_Swatch_Tile_SKU_37590E_Cone_05_6x6__61040.1663225337.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-318', 'Rose Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Rose Velvet underglaze is a deep magenta that is dark at cone 05, becomes patchy at cone 5 before it burns out almost completely at cone 10. A clear glaze over Rose will accentuate the color at cone 05 but at cone 5 and 10, there is no color change between glazed and unglazed.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/804/1484/37413P__92493.1659278074.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-320', 'Lavender Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Lavender velvet underglaze is a periwinkle color that is soft at cone 05, becomes deeper at cone 5, and burns out at cone 10. A clear glaze over Lavender will accentuate the color at cone 05 and 5 and preserves some bluish tones from the underglaze at cone 10.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/805/1482/37414R__48104.1659277884.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-321', 'Lilac Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Lilac velvet underglaze is a soft plum color that is light at cone 05 that becomes warmer and deeper at cone 5 and begins to burn out at cone 10. A clear glaze over Lilac will accentuate the color at cone 05 and 5 and will burn out a lot of the color at cone 10.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/806/1480/37415S__36342.1659277662.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-322', 'Purple Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Purple Velvet underglaze is a violet color that is soft at cone 05, becomes bluish and lighter at cone 5 before it becomes very light and blue at cone 10. A clear glaze over Purple will accentuate the color at cone 05 and cone 5 and causes more blue tones at cone 10.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/807/1478/37416T__55717.1659277509.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-323', 'Salmon Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Salmon Velvet underglaze is a soft peach color that is light at cone 05, becomes warmer and darker at cone 5, and maintains a toasted peach color at cone 10. A clear glaze over Salmon will accentuate and darken the color at cone 05, cone 5, and cone 10.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/808/1476/37417W__81771.1659277313.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-324', 'Blush Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Blush is a warm, soft pink underglaze that retains color from cone 05 up to cone 10 with minimal darkening. Clear glaze brightens the color. Blush underglaze can be used with zinc or non-zinc glazes without color shift.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2121/3318/V-324_Blush_Color_Swatch_Tile_SKU_37591F_Cone_05_6x6__70583.1663236644.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-325', 'Baby Blue Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Baby Blue Velvet underglaze is a soft light blue color that is bright and pastel at cone 05, becomes darker at cone 5, and is darker sky blue at cone 10. A clear glaze over Baby blue will accentuate the color at cone 05 but begins to burn out some of the color at cone 5 and cone 10.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/809/1473/37418X__22466.1659277129.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-326', 'Medium Blue Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Medium Blue Velvet Underglaze is a brilliant primary blue that is vivid at cone 05, darker at cone 5, maintaining its blue color. A clear glaze over Medium Blue will significantly darken the color at any temperature.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2122/3321/37419Y__43158.1663237160.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-327', 'Turquoise Blue Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Turquoise Blue Velvet underglaze is a blue green color that is cyan at cone 05, becomes deeper cone 5, and becomes very dark at cone 10. This underglaze maintains its color well under a clear glaze at any temperature.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/811/1469/37420A__69540.1659276837.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-328', 'Iceberg Blue Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Iceberg Blue Velvet underglaze is a light blue color that is powder blue at cone 05, becomes slightly darker at cone 5, and maintains its light blue shade up to cone 10. A clear glaze over Iceberg Blue tends to lift the color out slightly, lightening it.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/812/1467/37421B__02322.1659276681.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-329', 'Sea Glass Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Sea Glass is a very pale blue-green color at cone 05 and becomes richer and darker under a clear glaze. It remains the same at cone 5, but fired to cone 10 becomes more blue.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2279/3650/V-329_SeaGlass_Cone05_WebsiteSwatch__86153.1707235347.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-330', 'Indigo Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Indigo is a deep purple-blue color at cone 05 and darkens under a clear glaze. When fired to cone 5, it becomes more blue in color and then darkens slightly at cone 10.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2280/3653/V-330_Indigo_Cone05_WebsiteSwatch__74702.1707238210.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-332', 'Teal Blue Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Teal Blue underglaze is a deep blue color that is rich sapphire at cone 05 that becomes a deep medium blue at cone 5, and is very dark at cone 10. A clear glaze over Teal Blue will drastically darken its color at any temperature.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/813/1466/37422C__18559.1659276467.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-333', 'Avocado Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Avocado Velvet Underglaze is a pea green color that is vivid at cone 05, darkens at cone 5 and becomes a deep chartreuse at cone 10. A clear glaze deepens the color of the underglaze significantly at any temperature For Avocado Velvet Underglaze, we recommend using HF-9 Zinc Free Clear. If HF-10 Clear is used, color may shift HF-9 Zinc-Free Clear is recommended for use with underglazes to reduce the incidence of color shift. Most underglazes, stains, and coloring oxides will show their best color with Zinc-Free Clear.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/814/1464/37423D__90259.1659276334.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-336', 'Royal Blue Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Royal Blue Velvet Underglaze is a navy blue that is deep and saturated at cone 05, darkens at cone 5, and becomes almost black at cone 10. A clear glaze deepens the color of the underglaze significantly at any temperature.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/816/1462/37425F__12297.1659275964.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-341', 'Blue Green Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Blue Green Velvet Underglaze is a teal color that is deep aqua at cone 05, darkens at cone 5, and becomes a dark marine blue at cone 10. A clear glaze deepens the color of the underglaze significantly at any temperature.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/817/1460/37426G__14937.1659275890.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-343', 'Chartreuse Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Chartreuse Velvet Underglaze is a lime green color that is very bright at cone 05, softens to a mint green at cone 5, and darkens slightly at cone 10. A clear glaze accentuates the color of the underglaze significantly at any temperature.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/818/1458/37427H__40640.1659275824.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-345', 'Light Green Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Light Green Velvet Underglaze is a light spring green color that is bright at cone 05, darkens significantly to a forest green at cone 5, and becomes a deep pine green at cone 10. A clear glaze accentuates the color of the underglaze at any temperature.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/819/1455/37428J__29619.1659275683.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-347', 'Pistachio Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Pistachio is a light green underglaze that retains color from cone 05 up to cone 6 with minimal darkening. Above cone 6 the color becomes slightly bluer. Clear glaze brightens the color. Pistachio underglaze can be used with zinc or non-zinc glazes without color shift.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2123/3322/V-347_Pistachio_Color_Swatch_Tile_SKU_37592G_Cone_05_6x6__38469.1663254925.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-349', 'Cactus Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Cactus is a cool light green underglaze that retains color from cone 05 up to cone 6 with minimal darkening. Above cone 6 the color becomes slightly bluer. Clear glaze brightens the color. Cactus underglaze can be used with zinc or non-zinc glazes without color shift.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2124/3324/V-349_Cactus_Color_Swatch_Tile_SKU_37593H_Cone_05_6x6__97456.1663255185.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-350', 'Orange Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Orange Velvet Underglaze is a golden color that is bright at cone 05, softens to a toasty beige at cone 5, and becomes toastier at cone 10. A clear glaze accentuates the color of the underglaze significantly at any temperature.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/820/1454/37429K__16406.1659275611.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-353', 'Dark Green Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Dark Green Velvet Underglaze is a rich green color that is bright and saturated at cone 05, darkens to a forest green at cone 5, and becomes slightly darker at cone 10. A clear glaze deepens the color of the underglaze significantly at any temperature For Dark Green Velvet Underglaze, we recommend using HF-9 Zinc Free Clear. If HF-10 Clear is used, color may shift HF-9 Zinc-Free Clear is recommended for use with underglazes to reduce the incidence of color shift. Most underglazes, stains, and coloring oxides will show their best color with Zinc-Free Clear.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/821/1452/37430L__75615.1659275540.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-356', 'Pearl Gray Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Pearl Gray Velvet Underglaze is a bluish silver gray color that is bright at cone 05, darkens to a pewter tone at cone 5 and begins to lighten and burn out at cone 10. A clear glaze accentuates the color of the underglaze significantly at any temperature.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/824/1447/37433P__52647.1659275187.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-359', 'Ultra White Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Ultra White Velvet Underglaze is a bright and opaque white at cone 05, a frosty color at cone 5, and maintains its vividness at cone 10. A clear glaze accentuates the color of the underglaze significantly at any temperature.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2125/3327/V-359_Ultra_White_37625D_6x6_Square_TIle_Cone_05_WEB__00685.1663256246.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-360', 'White Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'White Velvet Underglaze is snow white color that is bright and minty at cone 05, softens at cone 5, and becomes slight warmer, but maintains a clean white color at cone 10. A clear glaze accentuates the underglaze at any temperature.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/826/1446/37435S__93969.1659275007.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-361', 'Jet Black Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Jet Black Velvet Underglaze is a cool black color that is smooth and velvety at cone 05, darkens at cone 5, and becomes darkest black and slightly glossy at cone 10. A clear glaze deepens and accentuates the underglaze significantly at any temperature Jet Black Velvet Underglaze may be muted when used under SM-10 Clear Satin SM-10 Clear Satin is a silky, stiff zinc-free clear glaze that works well as a liner or over underglazes. Use 2 coats over underglazes to show the color.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/827/1444/37437W__55283.1659274933.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-362', 'Ultra Black Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Ultra Black Velvet Underglaze fires to a beautiful soft, dark matte color at cone 05 then deepens to a darker black at cone 5 and maintains it’s shade at cone 10. A clear glaze accentuates the color of the underglaze significantly at any temperature Ultra Black Velvet Underglaze may be muted when used under SM-10 Clear Satin SM-10 Clear Satin is a silky, stiff zinc-free clear glaze that works well as a liner or over underglazes. Use 2 coats over underglazes to show the color.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2126/3329/V-362_Ultra_Black_37624C_6x6_Square_Tile_Cone_05_WEB__78748.1663257268.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-363', 'Morning Fog Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Morning Fog Velvet Underglaze fires to a light, misty gray when fired to cone 05, darkens to a steamy color at cone 5, and maintains the foggy color at cone 10. A clear glaze accentuates the color of the underglaze significantly at any temperature.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2127/3331/V-363_Morning_Fog_37621X_6x6_Square_Tile_Cone_05_WEB_(1)__16170.1663257618.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-364', 'Elephant Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Elephant Velvet Underglaze is a light, ashy shade when fired to cone 05, darkens to a deeper gray at cone 5 then turns to a grayish-black akin to elephant skin when fired to cone 10. A clear glaze accentuates the color of the underglaze significantly at any temperature.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2128/3333/V-364_Elephant_37622A_6x6_Square_Tile_Cone_05_WEB_(1)__48647.1663257851.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-365', 'Slate Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Slate Velvet Underglaze is a dark, bluish-gray at cone 05 that darkens to a deep, slatey shade when fired to cone 5 and transforms into a melancholic blue-green at cone 10. A clear glaze accentuates the color of the underglaze significantly at any temperature.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2129/3335/V-365_Slate_37623B_6x6_Square_Tile_Cone_05_WEB_(1)__82340.1663258190.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-366', 'Teddy Bear Brown', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Teddy Bear Velvet Underglaze is a chestnut color that is a warm tan at cone 05, darkens to a russet color at cone 5, and lightens and begins to burn out cone 10. A clear glaze accentuates the underglaze at cone 05 but burns out some of the color at cone 5 and cone 10 For Teddy Bear Velvet Underglaze, we recommend using HF-9 Zinc Free Clear. If HF-10 Clear is used, color may shift HF-9 Zinc-Free Clear is recommended for use with underglazes to reduce the incidence of color shift. Most underglazes, stains, and coloring oxides will show their best color with Zinc-Free Clear.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/828/1441/37439Y__17197.1659274782.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-370', 'Velour Black Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Velour Black Velvet Underglaze is a warm black color that is deep and velvety at cone 05, darkens and becomes warmer at cone 5, and is silky and deep at cone 10. A clear glaze deepens the color of the underglaze significantly at any temperature Velour Black Velvet Underglaze may be muted when used under SM-10 Clear Satin SM-10 Clear Satin is a silky, stiff zinc-free clear glaze that works well as a liner or over underglazes. Use 2 coats over underglazes to show the color.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/832/1440/37443D__95639.1659274410.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-375', 'Maroon Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Maroon Velvet Underglaze is a deep burgundy color that is soft and rich at cone 05, deepens at cone 5, and begins to burn out at cone 10. A clear glaze deepens the color of the underglaze significantly at cone 05 and intensifies its rich oxblood shade at cone 5.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/837/1436/37494B__99282.1659273846.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-376', 'Hunter Green Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Hunter Green Velvet Underglaze is an emerald color that is vivid at cone 05, darkens to a deep blue-green at cone 5, and becomes slightly darker and develops a sheen at cone 10. A clear glaze deepens the color of the underglaze significantly at any temperature For Hunter Green Velvet Underglaze, we recommend using HF-9 Zinc Free Clear. If HF-10 Clear is used, color may shift HF-9 Zinc-Free Clear is recommended for use with underglazes to reduce the incidence of color shift. Most underglazes, stains, and coloring oxides will show their best color with Zinc-Free Clear.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/838/1434/37495C__11360.1659273728.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-379', 'Ultra Violet Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Ultra Violet Velvet Underglaze is a soft, pinkish-purple at cone 05, darkens slightly at cone 5, then lightens when fired to cone 10 but still maintains its violet shade. A clear glaze accentuates the color of the underglaze significantly at any temperature.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2130/3337/V-379_Ultra_Violet_37620S_6x6_Square_Tile_Cone_05_WEB_(1)__73315.1663291538.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-380', 'Violet Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Violet Velvet Underglaze is a light plum color that is soft at cone 05, darkens at cone 5, and becomes a deep lilac color and begins to burn out at cone 10. A clear glaze accentuates the color of the underglaze nicely at any temperature.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/839/1430/37475D__31295.1659273576.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-381', 'Amethyst Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Amethyst Velvet Underglaze is a deep grape color that is vivid at cone 05, darkens at cone 5, and becomes a deep violet and begins to lose its color slightly at cone 10. A clear glaze deepens the color of the underglaze significantly at any temperature.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/840/1425/37476E__16359.1659273347.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-382', 'Red Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Red Velvet Underglaze is a crimson that is vivid at cone 05, deepens to a dark wine red at cone 5, and becomes brownish and begins to burn out at cone 10. A clear glaze accentuates the color of the underglaze nicely at cone 05 and cone 5.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/841/1422/37480J__44799.1659273243.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-383', 'Light Red Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Light Red Velvet Underglaze is a light coral red that is bright at cone 05, softens slightly at cone 5 and becomes darker and slightly glossy at cone 10. A clear glaze accentuates the color nicely at any temperature.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/842/1421/37482L__59867.1659273072.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-384', 'Real Orange Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Real Orange Velvet Underglaze is a luminous orange color that is bright and saturated at cone 05, softens and becomes lighter at cone 5 and becomes slightly warmer and is still bright at cone 10. A clear glaze accentuates the color of the underglaze significantly at any temperature.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/843/1419/37483M__09624.1659272892.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-385', 'Cinnamon Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Cinnamon Velvet Underglaze is a deep sienna color that is very warm at cone 05, darkens and becomes chocolatey at cone 5, and becomes a dark brown at cone 10. A clear glaze deepens the color of the underglaze significantly at any temperature.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/844/1417/37499G__67722.1659272719.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-386', 'Electric Blue Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Electric Blue Velvet Underglaze is a very deep cobalt blue that is vivid at cone 05, darkens significantly at cone 5, and becomes a very dark navy blue at cone 10. A clear glaze deepens the color of the underglaze significantly at any temperature.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/845/1415/37500H__52763.1659272626.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-387', 'Bright Red Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Bright Red Velvet Underglaze is a deep crimson color that is vivid at cone 05, darkens slightly at cone 5, and becomes a deep cherry red at cone 10. A clear glaze accentuates the underglaze significantly at any temperature For Bright Red Velvet Underglaze, we recommend using HF-10 Clear. HF-9 Zinc-Free Clear is recommended for use with underglazes to reduce the incidence of color shift. Most underglazes, stains, and coloring oxides will show their best color with Zinc-Free Clear.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2131/3339/37504M__36418.1663294250.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-388', 'Radiant Red Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Radiant Red Velvet Underglaze is a bright scarlet color that is vivid at cone 05, deepens at cone 5, and becomes slightly glossy and a deep fire-engine red at cone 10. A clear glaze accentuates the underglaze significantly at any temperature For Radiant Red Velvet Underglaze, we recommend using HF-10 Clear. HF-9 Zinc-Free Clear is recommended for use with underglazes to reduce the incidence of color shift. Most underglazes, stains, and coloring oxides will show their best color with Zinc-Free Clear.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/847/1406/37505N__64397.1659272262.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-389', 'Flame Orange Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Flame Orange Velvet Underglaze is a carrot color that is a bright red-orange at cone 05, darkens at cone 5, and becomes a deep persimmon color at cone 10. A clear glaze accentuates the underglaze significantly at any temperature For Flame Orange Velvet Underglaze, we recommend using HF-10 Clear. HF-9 Zinc-Free Clear is recommended for use with underglazes to reduce the incidence of color shift. Most underglazes, stains, and coloring oxides will show their best color with Zinc-Free Clear.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/848/1404/37506P__58786.1659272075.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-390', 'Bright Orange Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Bright Orange Velvet Underglaze is a tangerine color that is neon at cone 05, darkens slightly at cone 5 and becomes a deep pumpkin at cone 10. A clear glaze accentuates the underglaze significantly at any temperature For Bright Orange Velvet Underglaze, we recommend using HF-10 Clear. HF-9 Zinc-Free Clear is recommended for use with underglazes to reduce the incidence of color shift. Most underglazes, stains, and coloring oxides will show their best color with Zinc-Free Clear.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/849/1402/37507R__14731.1659271815.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-391', 'Intense Yellow Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Intense Yellow Velvet Underglaze is a bright pineapple color that is vivid at cone 05, deepens at cone 5, and is the deepest and most intense at cone 10. A clear glaze deepens the color of the underglaze significantly at any temperature For Intense Yellow Velvet Underglaze, we recommend using HF-10 Clear. HF-9 Zinc-Free Clear is recommended for use with underglazes to reduce the incidence of color shift. Most underglazes, stains, and coloring oxides will show their best color with Zinc-Free Clear.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/850/1400/37508T__59196.1659250604.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'AMACO', 'Velvet Underglaze', 'V-392', 'Blood Orange Underglaze', 'Cone 05 / Cone 06 / Cone 6 / Cone 10', 'Blood Orange is a fiery tangerine color at Cone 05 which intensifies under a clear glaze. When fired to Cone 5 and Cone 10, it becomes slightly darker.', 'https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-a0h9fhqogk/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/2281/3656/V-392_BloodOrange_Cone05_WebsiteSwatch__01108.1707239038.jpg?c=1'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Archie''s Glazes', 'MBG026', 'Gun Metal Green', 'Cone 6', 'One of our most popular and versatile glazes. A very runny, richly varied green that can be unpredictable, sometimes creating both matt and gloss areas on a single pot. Combines beautifully with almost all Coyote Glazes, and explodes with crystals in a slow cool. The Archie''s Series can be challenging to use, but rewards your skill with some of the most beautiful glazes available. They flow and interact with other colors dramatically, creating fantastic finishes unlike anything else possible in an electric kiln. They are also strongly affected by slow-cooling.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/RGGun%20Metal%20Green%20MBG026%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Archie''s Glazes', 'MBG028', 'Blue Purple', 'Cone 6', 'A pale blue with soft lavender tones and beautiful blue crystals. Looks different in each firing and explodes with crystals in a slow cool. Treat with care, it can be runny. The Archie''s Series can be challenging to use, but rewards your skill with some of the most beautiful glazes available. They flow and interact with other colors dramatically, creating fantastic finishes unlike anything else possible in an electric kiln. They are also strongly affected by slow-cooling.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/RGBlue%20Purple%20MBG028%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Archie''s Glazes', 'MBG031', 'Red Gold', 'Cone 6', 'One of our most beautiful and popular glazes. Red Gold is a golden cream color with streaks of reddish brown. Depending on the thickness and firing, it can achieve a wide range of colors and finishes, sometimes including blue crystals. It can be very runny. The Archie''s Series can be challenging to use, but rewards your skill with some of the most beautiful glazes available. They flow and interact with other colors dramatically, creating fantastic finishes unlike anything else possible in an electric kiln. They are also strongly affected by slow-cooling.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/RGRed%20Gold%20MBG031%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Archie''s Glazes', 'MBG034', 'Archie''s Base', 'Cone 6', 'A runny but beautiful glaze. Pale pink or sometimes cream colored on its own, the Archie''s really shines when combined with other glazes, changing their colors and pulling them into interesting new patterns. The Archie''s Series can be challenging to use, but rewards your skill with some of the most beautiful glazes available. They flow and interact with other colors dramatically, creating fantastic finishes unlike anything else possible in an electric kiln. They are also strongly affected by slow-cooling.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/RGArchie''s%20Base%20MBG034%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Archie''s Glazes', 'MBG055', 'Opal', 'Cone 6', 'Possibly our runniest glaze, but also one of our most beautiful. Opal is a brilliant pearlescent blue that varies from translucent where thin to mottled where thick. The Archie''s Series can be challenging to use, but rewards your skill with some of the most beautiful glazes available. They flow and interact with other colors dramatically, creating fantastic finishes unlike anything else possible in an electric kiln. They are also strongly affected by slow-cooling.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/RGOpal%20MBG055%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Archie''s Glazes', 'MBG056', 'Eggplant', 'Cone 6', 'One of our most varied and exciting glazes, Eggplant breaks from matt purple to glossy green, and develops intense blue crystals when it cools slowly. It can get runny, especially when extra thick or hot. The Archie''s Series can be challenging to use, but rewards your skill with some of the most beautiful glazes available. They flow and interact with other colors dramatically, creating fantastic finishes unlike anything else possible in an electric kiln. They are also strongly affected by slow-cooling.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/RGEggplant%20MBG056%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Archie''s Glazes', 'MBG057', 'Rhubarb', 'Cone 6', 'A beautiful, but runny, glaze, similar to the Archie''s Base but more reliably pink. Combines well with any Coyote glaze. The Archie''s Series can be challenging to use, but rewards your skill with some of the most beautiful glazes available. They flow and interact with other colors dramatically, creating fantastic finishes unlike anything else possible in an electric kiln. They are also strongly affected by slow-cooling.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/Pots/rhubarb/thumbs/RGRhubarb%20MBG057%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Archie''s Glazes', 'MBG058', 'Ice Blue', 'Cone 6', 'A runny but beautiful pale blue glaze. Icy blue crystals appear frequently in this glaze, especially when it is slow cooled. The Archie''s Series can be challenging to use, but rewards your skill with some of the most beautiful glazes available. They flow and interact with other colors dramatically, creating fantastic finishes unlike anything else possible in an electric kiln. They are also strongly affected by slow-cooling.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/RGIce%20Blue%20MBG058%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Archie''s Glazes', 'MBG240', 'Frosted Topaz', 'Cone 6', 'The Archie''s Series can be challenging to use, but rewards your skill with some of the most beautiful glazes available. They flow and interact with other colors dramatically, creating fantastic finishes unlike anything else possible in an electric kiln. They are also strongly affected by slow-cooling.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/2021/Tiles/FrostedTopaz.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Archie''s Glazes', 'MBG241', 'Magenta Sky', 'Cone 6', 'The Archie''s Series can be challenging to use, but rewards your skill with some of the most beautiful glazes available. They flow and interact with other colors dramatically, creating fantastic finishes unlike anything else possible in an electric kiln. They are also strongly affected by slow-cooling.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/2021/Tiles/MagentaSky.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Archie''s Glazes', 'MBG242', 'Papaya', 'Cone 6', 'The Archie''s Series can be challenging to use, but rewards your skill with some of the most beautiful glazes available. They flow and interact with other colors dramatically, creating fantastic finishes unlike anything else possible in an electric kiln. They are also strongly affected by slow-cooling.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/2021/Tiles/Papaya.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Archie''s Glazes', 'MBG243', 'Parakeet Yellow', 'Cone 6', 'The Archie''s Series can be challenging to use, but rewards your skill with some of the most beautiful glazes available. They flow and interact with other colors dramatically, creating fantastic finishes unlike anything else possible in an electric kiln. They are also strongly affected by slow-cooling.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/2021/Tiles/ParakeetYellow.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Copper & Iron Glazes', 'MBG027', 'Toshi Brown', 'Cone 6', 'An iron glaze with a light brown to yellow-orange color. Often Toshi Brown will develop surface mottling similar to wood or salt fired glazes, without those special firing processes. One of our most varied series, the Copper and Iron Glazes provide beautiful, traditional looks for ceramic wares. They each have their own properties, but most are durable enough for functional ware.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/ICToshi%20Brown%20MBG027%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Copper & Iron Glazes', 'MBG032', 'Rust Brown', 'Cone 6', 'A light brown glaze with a mottled, satin surface. Less breaking than the Shino glazes but with more variation than the Satins. One of our most varied series, the Copper and Iron Glazes provide beautiful, traditional looks for ceramic wares. They each have their own properties, but most are durable enough for functional ware.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/ICRust%20Brown%20MBG032%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Copper & Iron Glazes', 'MBG035', 'Copper Blue', 'Cone 6', 'A somewhat runny, translucent glaze that pools in textured areas. Copper blue can serve as a nice base glaze, or sometimes an alternative to clear. Fires red in reduction. One of our most varied series, the Copper and Iron Glazes provide beautiful, traditional looks for ceramic wares. They each have their own properties, but most are durable enough for functional ware.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/Pots/copper%20blue/thumbs/ICCopper%20Blue%20MBG035%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Copper & Iron Glazes', 'MBG036', 'Crazed Copper', 'Cone 6', 'Very similar to Copper Blue, but lighter in color and covered in fine crazing on most clays. A somewhat runny, translucent glaze that pools in textured areas. Fires red in reduction. One of our most varied series, the Copper and Iron Glazes provide beautiful, traditional looks for ceramic wares. They each have their own properties, but most are durable enough for functional ware.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/ICCrazed%20Copper%20MBG036%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Copper & Iron Glazes', 'MBG037', 'Oasis', 'Cone 6', 'A bright electric blue, with a slight translucency when thin, and a deep mottled look over black. One of our most varied series, the Copper and Iron Glazes provide beautiful, traditional looks for ceramic wares. They each have their own properties, but most are durable enough for functional ware.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/ICOasis%20MBG037.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Copper & Iron Glazes', 'MBG040', 'Saturated Iron', 'Cone 6', 'A rich, dark iron glaze. Usually has a smooth, deep brown surface, but can also become reddish, especially when slow cooled. One of our most varied series, the Copper and Iron Glazes provide beautiful, traditional looks for ceramic wares. They each have their own properties, but most are durable enough for functional ware.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/ICSaturated%20Iron%20MBG040%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Copper & Iron Glazes', 'MBG120', 'Bronze Temmoku', 'Cone 6', 'A dramatic glaze that emulates the look of a gas-fired temmoku when used on a red clay, but produces a beautiful shimmering bronze on white clays. Also looks great combined with the gloss or satin glazes. One of our most varied series, the Copper and Iron Glazes provide beautiful, traditional looks for ceramic wares. They each have their own properties, but most are durable enough for functional ware.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/ICBronze%20Temmoku%20MBG120%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Copper & Iron Glazes', 'MBG130', 'Snowy Plum', 'Cone 6', 'A specialized glaze with a carefully balanced formula, creating true reduction copper red in your electric kiln. Snowy Plum uses a chemical that reduces the glaze locally, and must be applied very thick for the reduction to work. Care should be taken to prevent running. One of our most varied series, the Copper and Iron Glazes provide beautiful, traditional looks for ceramic wares. They each have their own properties, but most are durable enough for functional ware.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/ICSnowy%20Plum%20MBG130%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Copper & Iron Glazes', 'MBG131', 'Oxblood', 'Cone 6', 'A specialized glaze, Oxblood contains a chemical that causes it to reduce locally, producing a true copper red in your electric kiln without a special firing. Because of the way this glaze works, it needs to be very thick to produce the red color. Thinner spots will be clear or grayish. One of our most varied series, the Copper and Iron Glazes provide beautiful, traditional looks for ceramic wares. They each have their own properties, but most are durable enough for functional ware.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/ICOxblood%20MBG131%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG160', 'Ivory Crystal', 'Cone 6', 'A beautiful glaze with white and transparent tones, which grows large white and gold crystals when slow cooled. Ivory Crystal is perfect for elegant forms like vases and decorative bottles. Crystals grow best on smooth surfaces. Crystalline Slow Cool Glazes are a great way to add exciting new details to your work. They are less runny than traditional crystal glazes, removing the need for a drip tray, and can be fired with other, non-crystal glazes. They do still run, so take care with your application!', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SLIvory%20Crystal%20MBG160%20SC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG161', 'Crystal Celadon', 'Cone 6', 'A translucent soft green with pale crystals. Crystals grow best on smooth, white clay. Crystalline Slow Cool Glazes are a great way to add exciting new details to your work. They are less runny than traditional crystal glazes, removing the need for a drip tray, and can be fired with other, non-crystal glazes. They do still run, so take care with your application!', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SLCrystal%20Celadon%20MBG161%20SC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG162', 'Crystal Lagoon', 'Cone 6', 'One of the most dramatic glazes available, Crystal Lagoon varies from deep cobalt blue where thick to brown where thin, and grows large blue crystals when slow cooled. Crystalline Slow Cool Glazes are a great way to add exciting new details to your work. They are less runny than traditional crystal glazes, removing the need for a drip tray, and can be fired with other, non-crystal glazes. They do still run, so take care with your application!', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/Crystal%20Lagoon%20MBG162%20SC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG163', 'Crystal Aurora', 'Cone 6', 'A beautifully creamy and translucent glaze, with tones of purple and large blue crystals. One of the most popular of the Crystalline Slow Cools. Crystalline Slow Cool Glazes are a great way to add exciting new details to your work. They are less runny than traditional crystal glazes, removing the need for a drip tray, and can be fired with other, non-crystal glazes. They do still run, so take care with your application!', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SLCrystal%20Aurora%20MBG163%20SC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG164', 'Crystal Nebula', 'Cone 6', 'A beautiful translucent glaze with pale blue tones and gold colored crystals. Check out Ivory Crystal for a similar look without the blue. Crystalline Slow Cool Glazes are a great way to add exciting new details to your work. They are less runny than traditional crystal glazes, removing the need for a drip tray, and can be fired with other, non-crystal glazes. They do still run, so take care with your application!', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SLCrystal%20Nebula%20MBG164%20SC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG165', 'Rose Crystal', 'Cone 6', 'A pale translucent orange with large pink crystals. Rose Crystal is both cheerful and elegant. Perfect for decorative ware, especially over white clay. Crystalline Slow Cool Glazes are a great way to add exciting new details to your work. They are less runny than traditional crystal glazes, removing the need for a drip tray, and can be fired with other, non-crystal glazes. They do still run, so take care with your application!', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SLRose%20Crystal%20MBG165%20SC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG170', 'Autumn Spice', 'Cone 6', 'A satiny golden brown with a wonderful feel. Turns less reddish and more golden the slower it is cooled, and combines great with other glazes such as Light Gold. The Constellations are the first line of glazes designed to shine in both regular and slow-cooled firings. Thickness, firing temperature, and especially cooling speed can affect these glazes, ensuring they are never the same twice.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/COAutumn%20Spice%20MBG170%20SC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG171', 'Mars Red Iron', 'Cone 6', 'When fired in a regular cycle, the Mars Red Iron is a deep brownish red, similar to Saturated Iron. The slower it is cooled, the more intense it will become. The Constellations are the first line of glazes designed to shine in both regular and slow-cooled firings. Thickness, firing temperature, and especially cooling speed can affect these glazes, ensuring they are never the same twice.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/COMars%20Red%20Iron%20MBG171%20SC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG172', 'Light Gold', 'Cone 6', 'A variegated glaze with brown, orange, blue, and golden tones. Developed as an alternative to Red Gold for people who have problems using that glaze. The Constellations are the first line of glazes designed to shine in both regular and slow-cooled firings. Thickness, firing temperature, and especially cooling speed can affect these glazes, ensuring they are never the same twice.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SLLight%20Gold%20MBG172%20SC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG173', 'Summer Spice', 'Cone 6', 'A creamy brown glaze with reddish tones and touches of orange. Often develops tones of blue, especially when slow cooled. The Constellations are the first line of glazes designed to shine in both regular and slow-cooled firings. Thickness, firing temperature, and especially cooling speed can affect these glazes, ensuring they are never the same twice.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SLSummer%20Spice%20MBG173%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG174', 'Orion', 'Cone 6', 'The signature and most popular glaze of our Constellation Series, Orion is a beautiful glaze that varies from brown where thin, to bronze, to blue where thickest. When slow cooled, it is shot through with golden crystals. The Constellations are the first line of glazes designed to shine in both regular and slow-cooled firings. Thickness, firing temperature, and especially cooling speed can affect these glazes, ensuring they are never the same twice.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/COOrion%20MBG174%20SC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG175', 'Antares', 'Cone 6', 'A deep, intense blue. One of the most dramatic of the Constellation glazes, Antares will develop starry crystals and shades of bronze as it is cooled more slowly. The Constellations are the first line of glazes designed to shine in both regular and slow-cooled firings. Thickness, firing temperature, and especially cooling speed can affect these glazes, ensuring they are never the same twice.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/COAntares%20MBG175%20SC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG176', 'Andromeda', 'Cone 6', 'An astounding deep blue-green color with tones of brown where thin. Has a flowing look in a regular cool and gold crystals when slow-cooled. The Constellations are the first line of glazes designed to shine in both regular and slow-cooled firings. Thickness, firing temperature, and especially cooling speed can affect these glazes, ensuring they are never the same twice.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/COAndromeda%20MBG176%20SC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG177', 'Aquila', 'Cone 6', 'A golden brown with occasional purple and blue tones when slow cooled, and a greenish blue with brown tones when not. The Constellations are the first line of glazes designed to shine in both regular and slow-cooled firings. Thickness, firing temperature, and especially cooling speed can affect these glazes, ensuring they are never the same twice.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/COAquila%20MBG177%20SC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG178', 'Gemini', 'Cone 6', 'A brown glaze with blue tones when cooled quickly, and bronze tones when slow cooled. Looks vastly changed on different clays and at different thicknesses. The Constellations are the first line of glazes designed to shine in both regular and slow-cooled firings. Thickness, firing temperature, and especially cooling speed can affect these glazes, ensuring they are never the same twice.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/COGemini%20MBG178%20SC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG179', 'Aries', 'Cone 6', 'A shimmering green that can break brown where thin. Aries changes from glossy to matt when slow cooled, as tiny crystals grow across the surface. The Constellations are the first line of glazes designed to shine in both regular and slow-cooled firings. Thickness, firing temperature, and especially cooling speed can affect these glazes, ensuring they are never the same twice.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/COAries%20MBG179%20SC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG180', 'Honeydew', 'Cone 6', 'A beautiful bright green with a slight satiny finish. Great for indoor and outdoor tile, as well as functional ware. Holds up to nearly anything! Enduro-Color Glazes are designed for durability. They are perfect for liner glazes, standing up against fork and knife marking, dishwashers, and tomato stains. Enduro-Colors resist acid, chipping, crazing, scratching, staining, and all other hard use factors.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/180.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG181', 'Cool Artichoke', 'Cone 6', 'A stony greyish green with a super hard surface and a cool satin finish. Great for the inside and outside of dishes. Enduro-Color Glazes are designed for durability. They are perfect for liner glazes, standing up against fork and knife marking, dishwashers, and tomato stains. Enduro-Colors resist acid, chipping, crazing, scratching, staining, and all other hard use factors.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/181.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG182', 'Satin White Liner', 'Cone 6', 'Perfect for the insides of dishes, Satin White Liner is specially designed to resist crazing, staining, and everything else. Enduro-Color Glazes are designed for durability. They are perfect for liner glazes, standing up against fork and knife marking, dishwashers, and tomato stains. Enduro-Colors resist acid, chipping, crazing, scratching, staining, and all other hard use factors.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/182.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG183', 'Deep Avocado', 'Cone 6', 'A beautiful bright green with a slight satiny finish. Great for indoor and outdoor tile, as well as functional ware. Holds up to nearly anything! Enduro-Color Glazes are designed for durability. They are perfect for liner glazes, standing up against fork and knife marking, dishwashers, and tomato stains. Enduro-Colors resist acid, chipping, crazing, scratching, staining, and all other hard use factors.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/183.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG184', 'Cornsilk', 'Cone 6', 'A durable and inviting satin yellow. Resistant to staining, crazing and knife marking. Cadmium free. Enduro-Color Glazes are designed for durability. They are perfect for liner glazes, standing up against fork and knife marking, dishwashers, and tomato stains. Enduro-Colors resist acid, chipping, crazing, scratching, staining, and all other hard use factors.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/184.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG185', 'Walnut', 'Cone 6', 'A semi-gloss brown with lovely breaking and a super hard surface. Perfect for both functional and decorative ware. Enduro-Color Glazes are designed for durability. They are perfect for liner glazes, standing up against fork and knife marking, dishwashers, and tomato stains. Enduro-Colors resist acid, chipping, crazing, scratching, staining, and all other hard use factors.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/185.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG186', 'Gloss White Liner', 'Cone 6', 'A super durable glossy white glaze, perfect for porcelain. Gentle enough to let underglaze show through, but hard enough to repel acids and dishwashers. Enduro-Color Glazes are designed for durability. They are perfect for liner glazes, standing up against fork and knife marking, dishwashers, and tomato stains. Enduro-Colors resist acid, chipping, crazing, scratching, staining, and all other hard use factors.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/186.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG187', 'Apricot', 'Cone 6', 'A satiny color with a wonderfully unusual finish, soft to the touch but hard against cutlery marking. Apricot is one of the most popular of our Enduro-Color line, a warm stony pink perfect for dishes or tiles. Enduro-Color Glazes are designed for durability. They are perfect for liner glazes, standing up against fork and knife marking, dishwashers, and tomato stains. Enduro-Colors resist acid, chipping, crazing, scratching, staining, and all other hard use factors.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/187.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG188', 'Sweet Plum', 'Cone 6', 'A lovely glossy purple that sometimes breaks to green where thinnest. Enduro-Color Glazes are designed for durability. They are perfect for liner glazes, standing up against fork and knife marking, dishwashers, and tomato stains. Enduro-Colors resist acid, chipping, crazing, scratching, staining, and all other hard use factors.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/188.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG189', 'Beechnut', 'Cone 6', 'A pale brown with some breaking. Ideal for the inside and outside of dishes, or anything else needing a durable surface. Enduro-Color Glazes are designed for durability. They are perfect for liner glazes, standing up against fork and knife marking, dishwashers, and tomato stains. Enduro-Colors resist acid, chipping, crazing, scratching, staining, and all other hard use factors.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/189.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG190', 'Summer Peach', 'Cone 6', 'A very subtle pink. Looks best on porcelain or other bright white clays. Enduro-Color Glazes are designed for durability. They are perfect for liner glazes, standing up against fork and knife marking, dishwashers, and tomato stains. Enduro-Colors resist acid, chipping, crazing, scratching, staining, and all other hard use factors.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/190.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Enduro-Color Glazes', 'MBG191', 'Blue Cornflower', 'Cone 6', 'A beautiful powdery blue with a super durable finish. Excellent for a liner or nearly any other use. Enduro-Color Glazes are designed for durability. They are perfect for liner glazes, standing up against fork and knife marking, dishwashers, and tomato stains. Enduro-Colors resist acid, chipping, crazing, scratching, staining, and all other hard use factors.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/191.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Fantasy Glazes', 'MBG210', 'Ancient Iron', 'Cone 6', 'A translucent brown with mesmerizing rivulets, Ancient Iron can display a dazzling array of colors. Under the right circumstances, amber, coffee, purple and blue tones can show across a surface, and gold crystals can even form in the areas where the glaze cools slowest. Fantasy Glazes can vary dramatically in appearance depending on the clay body used, the thickness of application, and in some cases, the firing. They can be runny, so it''s important to test carefully.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/Ancient%20Iron%20MBG210.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Fantasy Glazes', 'MBG211', 'Unicorn Horn', 'Cone 6', 'Unicorn Horn is one of the most versatile and surprising glazes we have ever made. Varying from pearlescent white, to mottled ivory, to ancient yellow, this magical glaze is perfect for buff clays with lots of texture. Fantasy Glazes can vary dramatically in appearance depending on the clay body used, the thickness of application, and in some cases, the firing. They can be runny, so it''s important to test carefully.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/Unicorn%20Horn%20MBG215.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Fantasy Glazes', 'MBG212', 'Enchanted Sunset', 'Cone 6', 'Varying from soft orange to a mottled pink, Enchanted Sunset is loaded with gorgeous microcrystals. The crystals and colors vary with thickness, creating a surface that draws the eye in deeper the longer you look. Fantasy Glazes can vary dramatically in appearance depending on the clay body used, the thickness of application, and in some cases, the firing. They can be runny, so it''s important to test carefully.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/Enchanted%20Sunset%20MBG212.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Fantasy Glazes', 'MBG213', 'Fairy Rose', 'Cone 6', 'A bright pink with delicate mottling, the intensity of Fairy Rose is mostly dependent on its thickness. Perfect for adding a bright accent to your work, Fairy Rose combines beautifully with other glazes. Fantasy Glazes can vary dramatically in appearance depending on the clay body used, the thickness of application, and in some cases, the firing. They can be runny, so it''s important to test carefully.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/Fairy%20Rose%20MBG213.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Fantasy Glazes', 'MBG214', 'Sorcerer''s Stone', 'Cone 6', 'A mottled charcoal gray that looks excellent on dinnerware, Sorcerer''s Stone is a consistent favorite at the Coyote studio. Depending on the clay it can vary from almost black to light gray, sometimes even breaking blue or brown on texture. Fantasy Glazes can vary dramatically in appearance depending on the clay body used, the thickness of application, and in some cases, the firing. They can be runny, so it''s important to test carefully.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/Sorceror''s%20Stone%20MBG214.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Fantasy Glazes', 'MBG216', 'Amethyst', 'Cone 6', 'A stunning multihued purple glaze with warm and cool tones blending into eachother like the last minutes of dusk. Fantasy Glazes can vary dramatically in appearance depending on the clay body used, the thickness of application, and in some cases, the firing. They can be runny, so it''s important to test carefully.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/2021/Tiles/Amethyst.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Fantasy Glazes', 'MBG217', 'Antique Pearl', 'Cone 6', 'Fantasy Glazes can vary dramatically in appearance depending on the clay body used, the thickness of application, and in some cases, the firing. They can be runny, so it''s important to test carefully.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/2021/Tiles/AntiquePearl.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Fantasy Glazes', 'MBG218', 'Dragon''s Eye', 'Cone 6', 'Fantasy Glazes can vary dramatically in appearance depending on the clay body used, the thickness of application, and in some cases, the firing. They can be runny, so it''s important to test carefully.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/2021/Tiles/DragonsEye.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Fantasy Glazes', 'MBG219', 'Firefly Garden', 'Cone 6', 'Fantasy Glazes can vary dramatically in appearance depending on the clay body used, the thickness of application, and in some cases, the firing. They can be runny, so it''s important to test carefully.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/2021/Tiles/FireflyGarden.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Fantasy Glazes', 'MBG220', 'Hydra Scale', 'Cone 6', 'Fantasy Glazes can vary dramatically in appearance depending on the clay body used, the thickness of application, and in some cases, the firing. They can be runny, so it''s important to test carefully.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/2021/Tiles/HydraScale.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG098', 'Dusty Rose', 'Cone 6', 'A translucent pink that won''t cover underglaze. Develops a slightly bluish haze where thickest. Great for any application, though colors show best on white clays. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/CLDusty%20Rose%20MBG098%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG099', 'Sedona Sunset', 'Cone 6', 'A bright, translucent color that adds warmth to any piece without hiding detail. Easy to apply and reliable. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/Pots/sedona%20sunset/thumbs/CLSedona%20Sunset%20MBG099%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG100', 'Peach Blush', 'Cone 6', 'A translucent pale pink. A unique and warm alternative to traditional celadon finishes, Peach Blush is perfect for porcelain. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/CLPeach%20Blush%20MBG100%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG101', 'Stormy Sea', 'Cone 6', 'A deep gray-green Celadon with deeper green tones and splashes of blue where thickest. Great for any work with texture or underglazes Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/CLStormy%20Sea%20MBG101%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG102', 'Aqua', 'Cone 6', 'A gentle, translucent blue-green color, similar to a traditional celadon. Easy to apply and reliable. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/CLAqua%20MBG102%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG103', 'Key Lime', 'Cone 6', 'A translucent green, great for any piece with texture or underglaze. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/CLKey%20Lime%20MBG103%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG104', 'Peacock Green', 'Cone 6', 'Our best-selling Celadon! A deep translucent green, which pools to a cloudy blue where thickest. Peacock Green is not recommended for food ware, as it can change color when exposed to acids such as lemon or vinegar. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/CLPeacock%20Green%20MBG104%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG105', 'Root Beer', 'Cone 6', 'A translucent brown that pools beautifully. Varies from caramel to deep chestnut depending on the thickness. Unlike the other Celadons, Root Beer can be a bit runny. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They look great on their own or combined with other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/CLRoot%20Beer%20MBG105%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG106', 'Sunshine Yellow', 'Cone 6', 'A bright, translucent yellow. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/CLSunshine%20Yellow%20MBG106%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG107', 'Night Sky', 'Cone 6', 'A translucent greenish gray, which develops a blue haze where it is thickest. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/CLNight%20Sky%20MBG107%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG108', 'Sapphire', 'Cone 6', 'A deep, clear blue. Translucent enough to be used over fine details or underglaze, Sapphire starts as a pale blue and becomes darker as it pools. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/CLSapphire%20MBG108%20RC.jpg'),
