  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG114', 'Sky', 'Cone 6', 'A translucent light blue. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250 Tiles/Sky copy.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG115', 'Tangerine', 'Cone 6', 'A translucent bright orange. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250 Tiles/Tangerine copy.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Frank''s Colored Celadon Glazes', 'MBG116', 'Midnight Rain', 'Cone 6', 'A translucent deep blue. Frank''s Colored Celadons are a beautiful series of translucent glazes. Because they can be seen through, they are perfect for work with fine details or carving, or as an alternative to clear for ware with underglaze. They do not run and look great on their own or combined with other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250 Tiles/Midnight Rain copy.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG001', 'Almost Teal', 'Cone 6', 'A deep blue with a smooth, glossy surface. As easy to use as it is beautiful, Almost Teal is one of the most popular starting points for glaze combinations. Great for beginners and advanced potters alike. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/GLAlmost%20Teal%20MBG001%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG002', 'Black', 'Cone 6', 'A solid, opaque black with a smooth, glossy finish. Ideal for nearly any usage, on its own or combined with other glazes. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/GLBlack%20MBG002%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG005', 'Chrome Green', 'Cone 6', 'A solid, unbreaking green. The pigment in Chrome Green will react with Archie''s Base and cause it to flash pink, making this color a great choice for combining with that series. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/GLChrome%20Green%20MBG005%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG006', 'Cinnamon Stick', 'Cone 6', 'A rich glossy brown. Great on its own or combined with the Archie''s series, Cinnamon Stick develops a slight bluish haze at its thickest. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/GLCinnamon%20Stick%20MBG006.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG007', 'Clear', 'Cone 6', 'The perfect cover for underglaze, Coyote Clear Glaze is zinc-free and can be used over pinks and reds without damaging them. With proper application and firing, it provides a totally clear glassy surface. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/GLClear%20MBG007%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG008', 'Cobalt Blue', 'Cone 6', 'A deep and intense blue that becomes darker as it gets thicker. Great for any use that calls for a darker color. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/GLCobalt%20Blue%20MBG008%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG011', 'Eggshell', 'Cone 6', 'A stable and reliable glaze that is less bright than White, but has the same glossy finish. Great as a liner glaze for functional ware. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/GLEggshell%20MBG011%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG013', 'Light Blue', 'Cone 6', 'A glossy, translucent blue. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/GLLight%20Blue%20MBG013%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG015', 'Mint', 'Cone 6', 'A light seafoam green. Looks lovely with Shino glazes, or on its own for a bright glossy finish. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/GLMint%20MBG015%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG017', 'Red Orange', 'Cone 6', 'A bright red-orange glossy glaze. Doesn''t run and provides a smooth, bold color. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/GLRed%20Orange%20MBG017%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG019', 'Red', 'Cone 6', 'A deep, intense red with less brightness and a more natural tone compared to our Really Red. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/GLRed%20MBG019%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG020', 'Orange', 'Cone 6', 'A warm glossy orange. Great on any pot, and combines with any glaze. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/GLOrange%20MBG020%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG023', 'White', 'Cone 6', 'A glossy, bright white, with a smooth surface. Won''t run, works great on its own or as a base for other glazes. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/GLWhite%20MBG023%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG025', 'Yellow Orange', 'Cone 6', 'A yellow orange glossy glaze that doesn''t run. Try firing it in a cone 6 soda kiln for a truly transformative look. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/GLYellow%20Orange%20MBG025%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG048', 'Oatmeal', 'Cone 6', 'A glossy off-white flecked with dark brown specks. Has a smooth, glossy surface when fired. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/GLOatmeal%20MBG048%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG050', 'Buttercup', 'Cone 6', 'A bright, cheerful yellow. Perfect as an accent color, or as a contrasting layer to dark colors like Blue Shino or Espresso Bean. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/GLButtercup%20MBG050%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG051', 'Pumpkin', 'Cone 6', 'A glossy opaque orange with lovely reddish tones. Won''t run, glossy finish. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/GLPumpkin%20MBG051%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG053', 'Pansy Purple', 'Cone 6', 'A deep, dark, intense purple color, the "really purple" answer to our Really Red glaze. Provides a solid, unbreaking finish. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/GLPansy%20Purple%20MBG053%20R.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG054', 'Violet', 'Cone 6', 'A light but vibrant purple. Perfect for adding warmth to a piece. Potters looking for a more intense purple should look at Pansy Purple, as well. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/GLViolet%20MBG054%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Gloss Glazes', 'MBG071', 'Really Red', 'Cone 6', 'One of our most famous glazes, a true, bright red that won''t quit. Truly eye-catching, and great as an accent or across a whole piece. Coyote Gloss Glazes provide bold, bright, solid colors for your ware. Durable and not runny, these glazes are equally suited to both decorative and practical ware. They combine great with other Coyote glazes, especially the Archie''s and Shino series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/GLReally%20Red%20MBG071%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Matt Glazes & Crawl Glazes', 'MBG024', 'Blue Matt', 'Cone 6', 'A soft blue that can sometimes be yellowish-brown when thin. Perfect for nearly any non-functional ware, this glaze absorbs light in a striking way and feels warm and dry to the touch. Our Matt glazes are a favorite series for sculptors everywhere. They provide a strong color tone and nice variety without a glossy finish. They are very stable and reliable, almost never running or behaving unexpectedly.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/Pots/blue%20matt/thumbs/MABlue%20Matt%20MBG024%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Matt Glazes & Crawl Glazes', 'MBG029', 'Creamy Matt', 'Cone 6', 'A creamy off-white with a flat finish. Unlike most of the other Matt glazes, Creamy Matt is tough enough to resist scratches from silverware, and so is suitable for functional ware when properly applied and fired. Our Matt glazes are a favorite series for sculptors everywhere. They provide a strong color tone and nice variety without a glossy finish. They are very stable and reliable, almost never running or behaving unexpectedly.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/MACreamy%20Matt%20MBG029%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Matt Glazes & Crawl Glazes', 'MBG030', 'Creamy Matt W/ Specks', 'Cone 6', 'A favorite glaze of potters of all stripes. Creamy with Specks is the same durable off-white color as the original Creamy Matt, but with additional dark specks that add variation to the surface. Our Matt glazes are a favorite series for sculptors everywhere. They provide a strong color tone and nice variety without a glossy finish. They are very stable and reliable, almost never running or behaving unexpectedly.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/MACreamy%20Matt%20w%20Specks%20MBG030%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Matt Glazes & Crawl Glazes', 'MBG033', 'Turquoise Matt', 'Cone 6', 'A deep turquoise color, rough to the touch. Perfect for small accents, or to add a field to a decorative piece. Our Matt glazes are a favorite series for sculptors everywhere. They provide a strong color tone and nice variety without a glossy finish. They are very stable and reliable, almost never running or behaving unexpectedly.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/MATurquoise%20Matt%20MBG033%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Matt Glazes & Crawl Glazes', 'MBG047', 'Green Matt', 'Cone 6', 'One of the most popular glazes in the Matt Series, Green Matt has a nicely variegated surface that breaks from green to black. Our Matt glazes are a favorite series for sculptors everywhere. They provide a strong color tone and nice variety without a glossy finish. They are very stable and reliable, almost never running or behaving unexpectedly.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/MAGreen%20Matt%20MBG047%20R.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Matt Glazes & Crawl Glazes', 'MBG049', 'Iron Matt', 'Cone 6', 'A neutral brown color with limited breaking. Our Matt glazes are a favorite series for sculptors everywhere. They provide a strong color tone and nice variety without a glossy finish. They are very stable and reliable, almost never running or behaving unexpectedly.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/MAIron%20Matt%20MBG049%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Matt Glazes & Crawl Glazes', 'MBG062', 'Blue Crawl', 'Cone 6', 'An exciting, exotic glaze that sometimes changes from blue to green depending on where it is placed in the kiln. Ideal for adding detail to sculptures, or as an unusual finish for non-functional ware. Perfect for potters looking for something unusual, our Crawl glazes have a tree-bark surface that''s rough and dry to the touch. To achieve the crawling effect, they must be applied very thick, until the dry surface of the glaze cracks before firing. They can also be used over underglazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/Pots/blue%20crawl/thumbs/CRBlue%20Crawl%20MBG062%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Matt Glazes & Crawl Glazes', 'MBG063', 'Cactus Crawl', 'Cone 6', 'A muted green that can add a unique look to any decorative ware. Cactus Crawl has an unusual but natural look, making it great for fountains and other outdoor features. Perfect for potters looking for something unusual, our Crawl glazes have a tree-bark surface that''s rough and dry to the touch. To achieve the crawling effect, they must be applied very thick, until the dry surface of the glaze cracks before firing. They can also be used over underglazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/CRCactus%20Crawl%20MBG063%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Matt Glazes & Crawl Glazes', 'MBG064', 'Chocolate Crawl', 'Cone 6', 'A chocolate brown glaze with a rough, irregular texture, similar to tree bark. Perfect for potters looking for something unusual, our Crawl glazes have a tree-bark surface that''s rough and dry to the touch. To achieve the crawling effect, they must be applied very thick, until the dry surface of the glaze cracks before firing. They can also be used over underglazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/CRChocolate%20Crawl%20MBG064%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Matt Glazes & Crawl Glazes', 'MBG065', 'Croc Crawl', 'Cone 6', 'A dark, scaly green like the skin of a crocodile. Great for sculptures and other decorative uses. Perfect for potters looking for something unusual, our Crawl glazes have a tree-bark surface that''s rough and dry to the touch. To achieve the crawling effect, they must be applied very thick, until the dry surface of the glaze cracks before firing. They can also be used over underglazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/CRCroc%20Crawl%20MBG065%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Matt Glazes & Crawl Glazes', 'MBG073', 'White Crawl', 'Cone 6', 'The simplest and most popular of our crawl glazes, White Crawl is great for any decoration that needs a dramatic surface. Perfect for potters looking for something unusual, our Crawl glazes have a tree-bark surface that''s rough and dry to the touch. To achieve the crawling effect, they must be applied very thick, until the dry surface of the glaze cracks before firing. They can also be used over underglazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/CRWhite%20Crawl%20MBG073%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Matt Glazes & Crawl Glazes', 'MBG110', 'Black Crawl', 'Cone 6', 'A much requested late addition to our Crawl Series, Black Crawl is a charcoal-colored glaze with a unique crackle pattern. Perfect for potters looking for something unusual, our Crawl glazes have a tree-bark surface that''s rough and dry to the touch. To achieve the crawling effect, they must be applied very thick, until the dry surface of the glaze cracks before firing. They can also be used over underglazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/CRBlack%20Crawl%20MBG110%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Mottled Glazes', 'MBG012', 'Fire Opal', 'Cone 6', 'A bright pink with a lovely haze where thick. Fire Opal is great on its own, and combines well with both the Gloss and Archie'' Series. The Mottled Series are designed to produce beautiful variegated colors with ease. Simple to apply and suitable for all types of ware, these colors are stunning on their own or combined with other glazes. They may appear thick in the jar and should be applied thick.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/MOFire%20Opal%20MBG012%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Mottled Glazes', 'MBG016', 'Mottled Blue', 'Cone 6', 'A base of black that turns a deep and variegated cobalt blue where thick. The Mottled Series are designed to produce beautiful variegated colors with ease. Simple to apply and suitable for all types of ware, these colors are stunning on their own or combined with other glazes. They may appear thick in the jar and should be applied thick.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/MOMottled%20Blue%20MBG016%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Mottled Glazes', 'MBG021', 'Sunset Pink', 'Cone 6', 'An intense mottled pink, with a paler pink haze where thick. Provides a smooth and glossy finish with a subtle intensity. The Mottled Series are designed to produce beautiful variegated colors with ease. Simple to apply and suitable for all types of ware, these colors are stunning on their own or combined with other glazes. They may appear thick in the jar and should be applied thick.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/MOSunset%20Pink%20MBG021%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Mottled Glazes', 'MBG038', 'Pam''s Green', 'Cone 6', 'One of our most popular glazes, especially when combined with the Archie''s Base. A deep, mottled green with a rich variegated surface. The Mottled Series are designed to produce beautiful variegated colors with ease. Simple to apply and suitable for all types of ware, these colors are stunning on their own or combined with other glazes. They may appear thick in the jar and should be applied thick.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/MOPam''s%20Green%20MBG038%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Mottled Glazes', 'MBG066', 'JB''s Brown', 'Cone 6', 'A rich, unbreaking brown. Where thickest, it develops a slight purplish haze. The Mottled Series are designed to produce beautiful variegated colors with ease. Simple to apply and suitable for all types of ware, these colors are stunning on their own or combined with other glazes. They may appear thick in the jar and should be applied thick.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/MOJB''s%20Brown%20MBG066%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Mottled Glazes', 'MBG070', 'Pam''s Blue', 'Cone 6', 'A mottled greyish blue. Provides the same surface variety as Pam''s Green, but with a less intense color. The Mottled Series are designed to produce beautiful variegated colors with ease. Simple to apply and suitable for all types of ware, these colors are stunning on their own or combined with other glazes. They may appear thick in the jar and should be applied thick.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/MOPam''s%20Blue%20MBG070%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Satin Glazes', 'MBG074', 'Alabaster Satin', 'Cone 6', 'A smooth, not quite glossy white, Alabaster Satin is ideal as a liner glaze for functional ware. Try using it with underglaze like a majolica base. Our Satin glazes have a soft, opaque surface that feels smooth to the touch. Durable, bright, and reliable, they are the perfect series for any functional potter seeking a contrast from more typical gloss glazes. They are not runny, are easy to use, and look great with the Archie''s series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SAAlabaster%20Satin%20MBG074%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Satin Glazes', 'MBG075', 'Baby Blue Satin', 'Cone 6', 'A bright blue that feels warm and soft. Doesn''t run, combines great with other colors, especially more mobile ones like the Archie''s Series. Our Satin glazes have a soft, opaque surface that feels smooth to the touch. Durable, bright, and reliable, they are the perfect series for any functional potter seeking a contrast from more typical gloss glazes. They are not runny, are easy to use, and look great with the Archie''s series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SABaby%20Blue%20Satin%20MBG075%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Satin Glazes', 'MBG076', 'Cerulean Satin', 'Cone 6', 'A deep blue that absorbs the light and draws the eye. Cerulean Satin works great on its own, and looks even better under Bronze Temmoku or Archie''s Base. Our Satin glazes have a soft, opaque surface that feels smooth to the touch. Durable, bright, and reliable, they are the perfect series for any functional potter seeking a contrast from more typical gloss glazes. They are not runny, are easy to use, and look great with the Archie''s series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SACerulean%20Satin%20MBG076%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Satin Glazes', 'MBG077', 'Charcoal Satin', 'Cone 6', 'A great alternative to Black for potters looking for less shine on their finished work. A natural looking dark charcoal color that absorbs light. Our Satin glazes have a soft, opaque surface that feels smooth to the touch. Durable, bright, and reliable, they are the perfect series for any functional potter seeking a contrast from more typical gloss glazes. They are not runny, are easy to use, and look great with the Archie''s series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SACharcoal%20Satin%20MBG077%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Satin Glazes', 'MBG078', 'Cherry Satin', 'Cone 6', 'A bright, true red. Similar to the Really Red glaze, but with a less glossy finish that absorbs the light. Our Satin glazes have a soft, opaque surface that feels smooth to the touch. Durable, bright, and reliable, they are the perfect series for any functional potter seeking a contrast from more typical gloss glazes. They are not runny, are easy to use, and look great with the Archie''s series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SACherry%20Satin%20MBG078%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Satin Glazes', 'MBG079', 'Coral Satin', 'Cone 6', 'A pinkish red with a buttery surface. Doesn''t break or run, combines great with other glazes. Our Satin glazes have a soft, opaque surface that feels smooth to the touch. Durable, bright, and reliable, they are the perfect series for any functional potter seeking a contrast from more typical gloss glazes. They are not runny, are easy to use, and look great with the Archie''s series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SACoral%20Satin%20MBG079%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Satin Glazes', 'MBG080', 'Forest Satin', 'Cone 6', 'A solid, unbreaking green. Forest Satin looks great on its own, or under other, runnier colors. Our Satin glazes have a soft, opaque surface that feels smooth to the touch. Durable, bright, and reliable, they are the perfect series for any functional potter seeking a contrast from more typical gloss glazes. They are not runny, are easy to use, and look great with the Archie''s series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SAForest%20Satin%20MBG080%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Satin Glazes', 'MBG081', 'Hazelnut Satin', 'Cone 6', 'An unbreaking brown, suitable for nearly any use. Our Satin glazes have a soft, opaque surface that feels smooth to the touch. Durable, bright, and reliable, they are the perfect series for any functional potter seeking a contrast from more typical gloss glazes. They are not runny, are easy to use, and look great with the Archie''s series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SAHazelnut%20Satin%20MBG081%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Satin Glazes', 'MBG082', 'Lapis Satin', 'Cone 6', 'A deep bluish purple with no breaking. Gun Metal Green and Lapis Satin is one of the most popular combinations of glaze, creating something unlike both colors. Our Satin glazes have a soft, opaque surface that feels smooth to the touch. Durable, bright, and reliable, they are the perfect series for any functional potter seeking a contrast from more typical gloss glazes. They are not runny, are easy to use, and look great with the Archie''s series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SALapis%20Satin%20MBG082%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Satin Glazes', 'MBG083', 'Lemon Cream Satin', 'Cone 6', 'A bright and unbreaking yellow, similar to Buttercup but without the glossy finish. Our Satin glazes have a soft, opaque surface that feels smooth to the touch. Durable, bright, and reliable, they are the perfect series for any functional potter seeking a contrast from more typical gloss glazes. They are not runny, are easy to use, and look great with the Archie''s series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SALemon%20Cream%20Satin%20MBG083.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Satin Glazes', 'MBG084', 'Orchid Satin', 'Cone 6', 'A warm purple, considerably brighter and less blue than the Lapis Satin. Orchid Satin''s bright tones and subtle surface make it a perfect contrast to darker, glossier glazes. Our Satin glazes have a soft, opaque surface that feels smooth to the touch. Durable, bright, and reliable, they are the perfect series for any functional potter seeking a contrast from more typical gloss glazes. They are not runny, are easy to use, and look great with the Archie''s series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SAOrchid%20Satin%20MBG084%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Satin Glazes', 'MBG085', 'Seafoam Satin', 'Cone 6', 'A bright bluish green with a smooth, buttery feel. Great as a slghtly calmer, less glossy alternative to Mint. Our Satin glazes have a soft, opaque surface that feels smooth to the touch. Durable, bright, and reliable, they are the perfect series for any functional potter seeking a contrast from more typical gloss glazes. They are not runny, are easy to use, and look great with the Archie''s series.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SASeafoam%20Satin%20MBG085%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG042', 'Shino', 'Cone 6', 'The original cone 6 Shino, sold by Coyote since 2002! A rich brown color that breaks darker over texture, giving an awesome gas-fired look in any kiln. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SHShino%20MBG042%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG043', 'Blue Shino', 'Cone 6', 'Dark blue where thick, reddish-brown where thinner. A rich glaze that looks great over texture or combined with other glazes. Contrasts great with bright colors like Buttercup. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SHBlue%20Shino%20MBG043%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG044', 'Green Shino', 'Cone 6', 'A dark green that breaks to brown over texture, and has a metallic sheen where thicker. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SHGreen%20Shino%20MBG044%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG045', 'Light Shino', 'Cone 6', 'A lighter version of our Shino glaze, Light Shino is a creamy beige where it pools, and breaks to a darker brown over texture. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SHLight%20Shino%20MBG045%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG059', 'Espresso Bean', 'Cone 6', 'A variegated black and brown color. Popular for combining with brighter colors like any dark Shino, or as a more natural looking alternative to Black. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SHEspresso%20Bean%20MBG059%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG061', 'Desert Sage', 'Cone 6', 'Varying from a sagebrush green to a dark reddish brown, Desert Sage is one of the most popular Shino Glazes. The natural green and brown tones look great on nearly any work. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SHDesert%20Sage%20MBG061%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG067', 'Light Blue Shino', 'Cone 6', 'In its thickest spots, Light Blue Shino is a pale blue, but where thinner it breaks to brown. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SHLight%20Blue%20Shino%20MBG067%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG068', 'Light Green Shino', 'Cone 6', 'A pale green that breaks to reddish brown over texture. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SHLight%20Green%20Shino%20MBG086%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG086', 'Butterscotch Shino', 'Cone 6', 'A neutral tone that breaks to dark brown over texture, and produces a marvellous furred pattern over Gloss glazes. A great glaze for adding warmth to textured pieces. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SHButterscotch%20Shino%20MBG086%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG087', 'Cedar Shino', 'Cone 6', 'A variegated reddish-brown that breaks over texture. Often attains a lacquer-like finish, but can turn glossy pink where thickest. Beatiful with Black. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SHCedar%20Shino%20MBG087%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG088', 'Goldenrod Shino', 'Cone 6', 'A warm yellow glaze that breaks to brown over texture. Breaks less than the other Shino Glazes, but still provides the same signature look. Great to layer with darker colors. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SHGoldenrod%20Shino%20MBG088%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG089', 'Leopard Shino', 'Cone 6', 'A slightly lighter shino dusted with orange-brown spots. Breaks to brown over texture, and combines with other glazes. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SHLeopard%20Shino%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG090', 'Mocha Shino', 'Cone 6', 'A beautiful glaze the color of coffee and cream, which breaks to dark brown where thin. Has a more satiny finish than most of the other Shinos. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SHMocha%20Shino%20MBG090%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG092', 'Plum Shino', 'Cone 6', 'A fairly muted purple that breaks brown over texture. The purple color will be most intense where the glaze is thickest. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SHPlum%20Shino%20MBG092%20R.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG093', 'Pistachio Shino', 'Cone 6', 'A mint green Shino glaze, breaking to brown where thinner. One of our most popular glazes! Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SHPistachio%20Shino%20MBG093%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG094', 'Sandstone Shino', 'Cone 6', 'A light brown with some cream tones, breaking darker brown over texture. Has a less glossy finish than most other Shino glazes, usually resulting in a nice satin. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SHSandstone%20Shino%20MBG094%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG096', 'Steel Gray Shino', 'Cone 6', 'A deep charcoal color that breaks black over texture. Can be glossy or satiny depending on the thickness and firing environment. Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SHSteel%20Gray%20Shino%20MBG096%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Shino Glazes', 'MBG097', 'Sunrise Shino', 'Cone 6', 'A warm color with pink and orange tones that breaks to brown where thin. Looks amazing over black! Our Shino glazes are gorgeous and most unusual, a rare combination of beauty and reliability. The color is sensitive to thickness, breaking brown where thinner and giving interest to the surface. Very user friendly, the Shinos are easy to apply, are not runny and are at their best over texture; they''re also great over other glazes.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/SHSunrise%20Shino%20MBG097%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Texas Two-Step Oilspot Glazes', 'MBG140', 'Licorice', 'Cone 6', 'A Texas Two-Step undercoat, designed to be used with the overcoats for oilspots. On its own, it is a mottled glossy black. The Texas Two-Step Oilspots are a specialized series that use pairs of glazes to create unique effects. Anywhere that one of the five overcoats is laid on top of Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red, a stunning spotted pattern will appear during firing. Thicker applications lead to bigger spots. Try using wax resist after the first layer to create negative space designs.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/TTLicorice%20MBG140%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Texas Two-Step Oilspot Glazes', 'MBG141', 'Coffee Bean', 'Cone 6', 'When covered by one of the Texas Two-Step overcoats, Coffee Bean produces the series signature oilspots. When used on its own, it is a darkly mottled brown, with a look similar to leather. The Texas Two-Step Oilspots are a specialized series that use pairs of glazes to create unique effects. Anywhere that one of the five overcoats is laid on top of Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red, a stunning spotted pattern will appear during firing. Thicker applications lead to bigger spots. Try using wax resist after the first layer to create negative space designs.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/TTCoffee%20Bean%20MBG141%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Texas Two-Step Oilspot Glazes', 'MBG142', 'Brick Red', 'Cone 6', 'A deep, solid red. Great on its own as a base or accent color, the Brick Red is a Texas Two-Step undercoat, and will create oilspot effects when covered with one of the overcoats. The Texas Two-Step Oilspots are a specialized series that use pairs of glazes to create unique effects. Anywhere that one of the five overcoats is laid on top of Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red, a stunning spotted pattern will appear during firing. Thicker applications lead to bigger spots. Try using wax resist after the first layer to create negative space designs.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/TTBrick%20Red%20MBG142%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Texas Two-Step Oilspot Glazes', 'MBG143', 'Fern', 'Cone 6', 'A bright sea green. Great on its own as a base or accent color, the Fern is a Texas Two-Step undercoat, and will create oilspot effects when covered with one of the overcoats. The Texas Two-Step Oilspots are a specialized series that use pairs of glazes to create unique effects. Anywhere that one of the five overcoats is laid on top of Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red, a stunning spotted pattern will appear during firing. Thicker applications lead to bigger spots. Try using wax resist after the first layer to create negative space designs.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250 Tiles/Fern copy.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Texas Two-Step Oilspot Glazes', 'MBG144', 'Mulberry', 'Cone 6', 'A deep dark purple. Great on its own as a base or accent color, the Mulberry is a Texas Two-Step undercoat, and will create oilspot effects when covered with one of the overcoats. The Texas Two-Step Oilspots are a specialized series that use pairs of glazes to create unique effects. Anywhere that one of the six overcoats is laid on top of an undercoat, a stunning spotted pattern will appear during firing. Thicker applications lead to bigger spots. Try using wax resist after the first layer to create negative space designs.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250 Tiles/Mulberry copy.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Texas Two-Step Oilspot Glazes', 'MBG145', 'Persimmon', 'Cone 6', 'A vivid orange. Great on its own as a base or accent color, the Persimmon is the brightest Texas Two-Step undercoat, and will create oilspot effects when covered with one of the overcoats. The Texas Two-Step Oilspots are a specialized series that use pairs of glazes to create unique effects. Anywhere that one of the six overcoats is laid on top of an undercoat, a stunning spotted pattern will appear during firing. Thicker applications lead to bigger spots. Try using wax resist after the first layer to create negative space designs.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250 Tiles/Persimmon copy.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Texas Two-Step Oilspot Glazes', 'MBG150', 'Blue Moon', 'Cone 6', 'Blue Moon is one of the Texas Two Step Overcoats, meaning it can be layered with Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red to produce an oilspot effect. It is also a beautiful soft blue on its own, making it suited to decorative and functional ware. The Texas Two-Step Oilspots are a specialized series that use pairs of glazes to create unique effects. Anywhere that one of the five overcoats is laid on top of Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red, a stunning spotted pattern will appear during firing. Thicker applications lead to bigger spots. Try using wax resist after the first layer to create negative space designs.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/Pots/blue%20moon/thumbs/TTBlue%20Moon%20MBG150%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Texas Two-Step Oilspot Glazes', 'MBG151', 'Birch', 'Cone 6', 'Birch is one of the Texas Two Step Overcoats, and can be layered with Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red to produce an oilspot effect. It can also be used on its own for a slightly mottled, neutral color. The Texas Two-Step Oilspots are a specialized series that use pairs of glazes to create unique effects. Anywhere that one of the five overcoats is laid on top of Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red, a stunning spotted pattern will appear during firing. Thicker applications lead to bigger spots. Try using wax resist after the first layer to create negative space designs.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/TTBirch%20MBG151%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Texas Two-Step Oilspot Glazes', 'MBG152', 'Texas Rose', 'Cone 6', 'Texas Rose is a lovely reddish pink, with an interesting mottling to the surface that can only be seen up close. It is also a Texas Two Step Overcoat, which can be layered with Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red to produce an oilspot effect. The Texas Two-Step Oilspots are a specialized series that use pairs of glazes to create unique effects. Anywhere that one of the five overcoats is laid on top of Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red, a stunning spotted pattern will appear during firing. Thicker applications lead to bigger spots. Try using wax resist after the first layer to create negative space designs.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/TTTexas%20Rose%20MBG152%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Texas Two-Step Oilspot Glazes', 'MBG153', 'Marshmallow', 'Cone 6', 'Marshmallow is one of the Texas Two Step Overcoats, meaning it can be layered with Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red to produce an oilspot effect. On its own, it is a glossy off-white, somewhere between Eggshell and Creamy Matt. The Texas Two-Step Oilspots are a specialized series that use pairs of glazes to create unique effects. Anywhere that one of the five overcoats is laid on top of Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red, a stunning spotted pattern will appear during firing. Thicker applications lead to bigger spots. Try using wax resist after the first layer to create negative space designs.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/TTMarshmallow%20MBG153%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Texas Two-Step Oilspot Glazes', 'MBG154', 'Sea Mist', 'Cone 6', 'Sea Mist is one of the Texas Two Step Overcoats, meaning it can be layered with Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red to produce an oilspot effect. When used alone, it is a mottled blue-green that can develop pale spots on its own. The Texas Two-Step Oilspots are a specialized series that use pairs of glazes to create unique effects. Anywhere that one of the five overcoats is laid on top of Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red, a stunning spotted pattern will appear during firing. Thicker applications lead to bigger spots. Try using wax resist after the first layer to create negative space designs.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/TTSea%20Mist%20MBG154%20RC.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Texas Two-Step Oilspot Glazes', 'MBG155', 'Clementine', 'Cone 6', 'Clementine is a bright orange that adds a warm pop to any palette. It is also a Texas Two Step Overcoat, which can be layered with one of the six Two Step Undercoats to produce an oilspot effect. The Texas Two-Step Oilspots are a specialized series that use pairs of glazes to create unique effects. Anywhere that one of the five overcoats is laid on top of Licorice, Coffee Bean, or Brick Red, a stunning spotted pattern will appear during firing. Thicker applications lead to bigger spots. Try using wax resist after the first layer to create negative space designs.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250 Tiles/Clementine copy.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Vibro-Color Glazes', 'MBG200', 'Mediterranean Sea', 'Cone 6', 'A beautiful glossy blue with a stain resistant finish that looks especially bright on white clays like B-Mix. Perfect for dishes, vases, tiles, and anything else. Vibro-Colors are as stable and reliable as Enduro-Color Liner Glazes, but loaded up with colorant for a vibrant pop. They do not run, resist scratching and crazing, and look pretty much the same in all firing cycles.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/Mediterranian%20Sea.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Vibro-Color Glazes', 'MBG201', 'Passion Red', 'Cone 6', 'A vivid red with a smooth glossy surface. Not only is Passion Red scratch resistant, stain resistant, and craze resistant, it''s also less prone to the pinhole problem that affects many other red glazes. Vibrant, beautiful, and easy to use, it''s quickly becoming a Coyote favorite. Vibro-Colors are as stable and reliable as Enduro-Color Liner Glazes, but loaded up with colorant for a vibrant pop. They do not run, resist scratching and crazing, and look pretty much the same in all firing cycles.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/Passion%20Red.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Vibro-Color Glazes', 'MBG202', 'Periwinkle', 'Cone 6', 'A pale lavender glaze with a lovely satin finish. Periwinkle should be applied heavily to ensure even coverage, as it can look a bit patchy where thin. When used correctly, it is a beautiful purplish blue ideal for homewares. Vibro-Colors are as stable and reliable as Enduro-Color Liner Glazes, but loaded up with colorant for a vibrant pop. They do not run, resist scratching and crazing, and look pretty much the same in all firing cycles.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/Periwinkle.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Vibro-Color Glazes', 'MBG203', 'Sundrop', 'Cone 6', 'Sundrop is a bright and cheery yellow with a hard glossy surface. It resists staining, scratching and crazing, while providing a warm vibrance to any piece. Vibro-Colors are as stable and reliable as Enduro-Color Liner Glazes, but loaded up with colorant for a vibrant pop. They do not run, resist scratching and crazing, and look pretty much the same in all firing cycles.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/Sundrop.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Vibro-Color Glazes', 'MBG204', 'Tiger Lily', 'Cone 6', 'Tiger Lily is a bright and cheery orange with a hard glossy surface. It resists staining, scratching and crazing, while providing a warm vibrance to any piece. Vibro-Colors are as stable and reliable as Enduro-Color Liner Glazes, but loaded up with colorant for a vibrant pop. They do not run, resist scratching and crazing, and look pretty much the same in all firing cycles.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/Tiger%20Lily.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Coyote', 'Vibro-Color Glazes', 'MBG205', 'Turquoise Lake', 'Cone 6', 'Maybe our most requested glaze, Turquoise Lake has the same color as our popular Turquoise Matt but in a smooth, glossy, and food safe finish! Vibro-Colors are as stable and reliable as Enduro-Color Liner Glazes, but loaded up with colorant for a vibrant pop. They do not run, resist scratching and crazing, and look pretty much the same in all firing cycles.', 'https://www.coyoteclay.com/Images/250%20Tiles/Turquoise%20Lake.jpg')
on conflict (brand, code) where created_by_user_id is null and code is not null
